116/* RECURSION_GUARD:
117 * the QStyleSheetStyle is a proxy. If used with others proxy style, we may end up with something like:
118 * QStyleSheetStyle -> ProxyStyle -> QStyleSheetStyle -> OriginalStyle
119 * Recursion may happen if the style call the widget()->style() again.
120 * Not to mention the performance penalty of having two lookup of rules.
121 *
122 * The first instance of QStyleSheetStyle will set globalStyleSheetStyle to itself. The second one
123 * will notice the globalStyleSheetStyle is not istelf and call its base style directly.
124 */
125static const QStyleSheetStyle *globalStyleSheetStyle = nullptr;
126class QStyleSheetStyleRecursionGuard
127{
128 public:
129 QStyleSheetStyleRecursionGuard(const QStyleSheetStyle *that)
130 : guarded(globalStyleSheetStyle == nullptr)
131 {
132 if (guarded) globalStyleSheetStyle = that;
133 }
134 ~QStyleSheetStyleRecursionGuard() { if (guarded) globalStyleSheetStyle = nullptr; }
135 bool guarded;
136};
137#define RECURSION_GUARD(RETURN) \
138 if (globalStyleSheetStyle != 0 && globalStyleSheetStyle != this) { RETURN; } \
139 QStyleSheetStyleRecursionGuard recursion_guard(this);

330struct QStyleSheetBackgroundData : public QSharedData

348};

350struct QStyleSheetBorderData : public QSharedData
351{
352 QStyleSheetBorderData() : bi(nullptr)
353 {
354 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
355 borders[i] = 0;
356 styles[i] = QCss::BorderStyle_None;
357 }
358 }
359
360 QStyleSheetBorderData(int *b, QBrush *c, QCss::BorderStyle *s, QSize *r) : bi(nullptr)
361 {
362 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
363 borders[i] = b[i];
364 styles[i] = s[i];
365 colors[i] = c[i];
366 radii[i] = r[i];
367 }
368 }
369
370 int borders[4];
371 QBrush colors[4];
372 QCss::BorderStyle styles[4];
373 QSize radii[4]; // topleft, topright, bottomleft, bottomright
374
375 const QStyleSheetBorderImageData *borderImage() const
376 { return bi; }
377 bool hasBorderImage() const { return bi!=nullptr; }
378
379 QSharedDataPointer<QStyleSheetBorderImageData> bi;
380
381 bool isOpaque() const
382 {
383 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
384 if (styles[i] == QCss::BorderStyle_Native || styles[i] == QCss::BorderStyle_None)
385 continue;
386 if (styles[i] >= QCss::BorderStyle_Dotted && styles[i] <= QCss::BorderStyle_DotDotDash
387 && styles[i] != BorderStyle_Solid)
388 return false;
389 if (!colors[i].isOpaque())
390 return false;
391 if (!radii[i].isEmpty())
392 return false;
393 }
394 if (bi != nullptr && bi->pixmap.hasAlpha())
395 return false;
396 return true;
397 }
398};

509 const QStyleSheetPaletteData *palette() const { return pal; }

518 bool hasModification() const;
519
520 bool hasPalette() const { return pal != nullptr; }
521 bool hasBackground() const { return bg != nullptr && (!bg->pixmap.isNull() || bg->brush.style() != Qt::NoBrush); }
522 bool hasGradientBackground() const { return bg && bg->brush.style() >= Qt::LinearGradientPattern
523 && bg->brush.style() <= Qt::ConicalGradientPattern; }
524
525 bool hasNativeBorder() const {
526 return bd == nullptr
527 || (!bd->hasBorderImage() && bd->styles[0] == BorderStyle_Native);
528 }
529
530 bool hasNativeOutline() const {
531 return (ou == nullptr
532 || (!ou->hasBorderImage() && ou->styles[0] == BorderStyle_Native));
533 }
534
535 bool baseStyleCanDraw() const {
536 if (!hasBackground() || (background()->brush.style() == Qt::NoBrush && bg->pixmap.isNull()))
537 return true;
538 if (bg && !bg->pixmap.isNull())
539 return false;
540 if (hasGradientBackground())
541 return features & StyleFeature_BackgroundGradient;
542 return features & StyleFeature_BackgroundColor;
543 }
544
545 bool hasBox() const { return b != nullptr; }
546 bool hasBorder() const { return bd != nullptr; }
547 bool hasOutline() const { return ou != nullptr; }
548 bool hasPosition() const { return p != nullptr; }
549 bool hasGeometry() const { return geo != nullptr; }
550 bool hasDrawable() const { return !hasNativeBorder() || hasBackground() || hasImage(); }
551 bool hasImage() const { return img != nullptr; }
552 bool hasIcon() const { return iconPtr != nullptr; }
553
554 QSize minimumContentsSize() const
555 { return geo ? QSize(geo->minWidth, geo->minHeight) : QSize(0, 0); }
556 QSize minimumSize() const
557 { return boxSize(s: minimumContentsSize()); }
558
559 QSize contentsSize() const
560 { return geo ? QSize(geo->width, geo->height)
561 : ((img && img->size.isValid()) ? img->size : QSize()); }
562 QSize contentsSize(const QSize &sz) const
563 {
564 QSize csz = contentsSize();
565 if (csz.width() == -1) csz.setWidth(sz.width());
566 if (csz.height() == -1) csz.setHeight(sz.height());
567 return csz;
568 }
569 bool hasContentsSize() const
570 { return (geo && (geo->width != -1 || geo->height != -1)) || (img && img->size.isValid()); }
571
572 QSize size() const { return boxSize(s: contentsSize()); }
573 QSize size(const QSize &sz) const { return boxSize(s: contentsSize(sz)); }
574 QSize adjustSize(const QSize &sz)
575 {
576 if (!geo)
577 return sz;
578 QSize csz = contentsSize();
579 if (csz.width() == -1) csz.setWidth(sz.width());
580 if (csz.height() == -1) csz.setHeight(sz.height());
581 if (geo->maxWidth != -1 && csz.width() > geo->maxWidth) csz.setWidth(geo->maxWidth);
582 if (geo->maxHeight != -1 && csz.height() > geo->maxHeight) csz.setHeight(geo->maxHeight);
583 csz=csz.expandedTo(otherSize: QSize(geo->minWidth, geo->minHeight));
584 return csz;
585 }

715static QList<QVariant> subControlLayout(const QString& layout)
716{
717 QList<QVariant> buttons;
718 for (int i = 0; i < layout.size(); i++) {
719 int button = layout[i].toLatin1();
720 switch (button) {
721 case 'm':
722 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_MdiMinButton);
723 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarMinButton);
724 break;
725 case 'M':
726 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarMaxButton);
727 break;
728 case 'X':
729 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_MdiCloseButton);
730 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarCloseButton);
731 break;
732 case 'N':
733 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_MdiNormalButton);
734 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarNormalButton);
735 break;
736 case 'I':
737 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarSysMenu);
738 break;
739 case 'T':
740 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBar);
741 break;
742 case 'H':
743 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarContextHelpButton);
744 break;
745 case 'S':
746 buttons.append(t: PseudoElement_TitleBarShadeButton);
747 break;
748 default:
749 buttons.append(t: button);
750 break;
751 }
752 }
753 return buttons;
754}

767QHash<QStyle::SubControl, QRect> QStyleSheetStyle::titleBarLayout(const QWidget *w, const QStyleOptionTitleBar *tb) const
768{
769 QHash<QStyle::SubControl, QRect> layoutRects;
770 const bool isMinimized = tb->titleBarState & Qt::WindowMinimized;
771 const bool isMaximized = tb->titleBarState & Qt::WindowMaximized;
772 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(w, tb);
773 QRect cr = subRule.contentsRect(r: tb->rect);
774 QList<QVariant> layout = subRule.styleHint(sh: "button-layout"_L1).toList();
775 if (layout.isEmpty())
776 layout = subControlLayout(layout: "I(T)HSmMX"_L1);
777
778 int offsets[3] = { 0, 0, 0 };
779 enum Where { Left, Right, Center, NoWhere } where = Left;
780 QList<ButtonInfo> infos;
781 const int numLayouts = layout.size();
782 infos.reserve(size: numLayouts);
783 for (int i = 0; i < numLayouts; i++) {
784 const int element = layout[i].toInt();
785 if (element == '(') {
786 where = Center;
787 } else if (element == ')') {
788 where = Right;
789 } else {
790 ButtonInfo info;
791 info.element = element;
792 switch (element) {
793 case PseudoElement_TitleBar:
794 if (!(tb->titleBarFlags & (Qt::WindowTitleHint | Qt::WindowSystemMenuHint)))
795 continue;
796 break;
797 case PseudoElement_TitleBarContextHelpButton:
798 if (!(tb->titleBarFlags & Qt::WindowContextHelpButtonHint))
799 continue;
800 break;
801 case PseudoElement_TitleBarMinButton:
802 if (!(tb->titleBarFlags & Qt::WindowMinimizeButtonHint))
803 continue;
804 if (isMinimized)
805 info.element = PseudoElement_TitleBarNormalButton;
806 break;
807 case PseudoElement_TitleBarMaxButton:
808 if (!(tb->titleBarFlags & Qt::WindowMaximizeButtonHint))
809 continue;
810 if (isMaximized)
811 info.element = PseudoElement_TitleBarNormalButton;
812 break;
813 case PseudoElement_TitleBarShadeButton:
814 if (!(tb->titleBarFlags & Qt::WindowShadeButtonHint))
815 continue;
816 if (isMinimized)
817 info.element = PseudoElement_TitleBarUnshadeButton;
818 break;
819 case PseudoElement_TitleBarCloseButton:
820 case PseudoElement_TitleBarSysMenu:
821 if (!(tb->titleBarFlags & Qt::WindowSystemMenuHint))
822 continue;
823 break;
824 default:
825 continue;
826 }
827 if (info.element == PseudoElement_TitleBar) {
828 info.width = tb->fontMetrics.horizontalAdvance(tb->text) + 6;
829 subRule.geo = new QStyleSheetGeometryData(info.width, tb->fontMetrics.height(), -1, -1, -1, -1);
830 } else {
831 subRule = renderRule(w, tb, info.element);
832 info.width = subRule.size().width();
833 }
834 info.rule = subRule;
835 info.offset = offsets[where];
836 info.where = where;
837 offsets[where] += info.width;
838
839 infos.append(t: std::move(info));
840 }
841 }
842
843 for (int i = 0; i < infos.size(); i++) {
844 const ButtonInfo &info = infos[i];
845 QRect lr = cr;
846 switch (info.where) {
847 case Center: {
848 lr.setLeft(cr.left() + offsets[Left]);
849 lr.setRight(cr.right() - offsets[Right]);
850 QRect r(0, 0, offsets[Center], lr.height());
851 r.moveCenter(p: lr.center());
852 r.setLeft(r.left()+info.offset);
853 r.setWidth(info.width);
854 lr = r;
855 break; }
856 case Left:
857 lr.translate(dx: info.offset, dy: 0);
858 lr.setWidth(info.width);
859 break;
860 case Right:
861 lr.moveLeft(pos: cr.right() + 1 - offsets[Right] + info.offset);
862 lr.setWidth(info.width);
863 break;
864 default:
865 break;
866 }
867 QStyle::SubControl control = knownPseudoElements[info.element].subControl;
868 layoutRects[control] = positionRect(w, rule2: info.rule, pe: info.element, originRect: lr, dir: tb->direction);
869 }
870
871 return layoutRects;
872}

892QRenderRule::QRenderRule(const QList<Declaration> &declarations, const QObject *object)
893 : features(0),
894 hasFont(false),
895 pal(nullptr),
896 b(nullptr),
897 bg(nullptr),
898 bd(nullptr),
899 ou(nullptr),
900 geo(nullptr),
901 p(nullptr),
902 img(nullptr),
903 clipset(0)
904{
905 QPalette palette = QGuiApplication::palette(); // ###: ideally widget's palette
906 ValueExtractor v(declarations, palette);
907 features = v.extractStyleFeatures();
908
909 int w = -1, h = -1, minw = -1, minh = -1, maxw = -1, maxh = -1;
910 if (v.extractGeometry(w: &w, h: &h, minw: &minw, minh: &minh, maxw: &maxw, maxh: &maxh))
911 geo = new QStyleSheetGeometryData(w, h, minw, minh, maxw, maxh);
912
913 int left = 0, top = 0, right = 0, bottom = 0;
914 Origin origin = Origin_Unknown;
915 Qt::Alignment position;
916 QCss::PositionMode mode = PositionMode_Unknown;
917 Qt::Alignment textAlignment;
918 if (v.extractPosition(l: &left, t: &top, r: &right, b: &bottom, &origin, &position, &mode, &textAlignment))
919 p = new QStyleSheetPositionData(left, top, right, bottom, origin, position, mode, textAlignment);
920
921 int margins[4], paddings[4], spacing = -1;
922 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
923 margins[i] = paddings[i] = 0;
924 if (v.extractBox(margins, paddings, spacing: &spacing))
925 b = new QStyleSheetBoxData(margins, paddings, spacing);
926
927 int borders[4];
928 QBrush colors[4];
929 QCss::BorderStyle styles[4];
930 QSize radii[4];
931 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
932 borders[i] = 0;
933 styles[i] = BorderStyle_None;
934 }
935 if (v.extractBorder(borders, colors, Styles: styles, radii))
936 bd = new QStyleSheetBorderData(borders, colors, styles, radii);
937
938 int offsets[4];
939 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
940 borders[i] = offsets[i] = 0;
941 styles[i] = BorderStyle_None;
942 }
943 if (v.extractOutline(borders, colors, Styles: styles, radii, offsets))
944 ou = new QStyleSheetOutlineData(borders, colors, styles, radii, offsets);
945
946 QBrush brush;
947 QString uri;
948 Repeat repeat = Repeat_XY;
949 Qt::Alignment alignment = Qt::AlignTop | Qt::AlignLeft;
950 Attachment attachment = Attachment_Scroll;
951 origin = Origin_Padding;
952 Origin clip = Origin_Border;
953 if (v.extractBackground(&brush, &uri, &repeat, &alignment, &origin, &attachment, &clip)) {
954 QPixmap pixmap = QStyleSheetStyle::loadPixmap(fileName: uri, context: object);
955 if (!uri.isEmpty() && pixmap.isNull())
956 qWarning(msg: "Could not create pixmap from %s", qPrintable(QDir::toNativeSeparators(uri)));
957 bg = new QStyleSheetBackgroundData(brush, pixmap, repeat, alignment, origin, attachment, clip);
958 }
959
960 QBrush sfg, fg, pfg;
961 QBrush sbg, abg;
962 if (v.extractPalette(fg: &fg, sfg: &sfg, sbg: &sbg, abg: &abg, pfg: &pfg))
963 pal = new QStyleSheetPaletteData(fg, sfg, sbg, abg, pfg);
964
965 QIcon imgIcon;
966 alignment = Qt::AlignCenter;
967 QSize imgSize;
968 if (v.extractImage(icon: &imgIcon, a: &alignment, size: &imgSize))
969 img = new QStyleSheetImageData(imgIcon, alignment, imgSize);
970
971 QIcon icon;
972 QSize size;
973 if (v.extractIcon(icon: &icon, size: &size))
974 iconPtr = new QStyleSheetImageData(icon, Qt::AlignCenter, size);
975
976 int adj = -255;
977 hasFont = v.extractFont(font: &font, fontSizeAdjustment: &adj);
978
979#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
980 if (object && qstrcmp(str1: object->metaObject()->className(), str2: "QTipLabel") == 0)
981 palette = QToolTip::palette();
982#endif
983
984 for (int i = 0; i < declarations.size(); i++) {
985 const Declaration& decl = declarations.at(i);
986 if (decl.d->propertyId == BorderImage) {
987 QString uri;
988 QCss::TileMode horizStretch, vertStretch;
989 int cuts[4];
990
991 decl.borderImageValue(image: &uri, cuts, h: &horizStretch, v: &vertStretch);
992 if (uri.isEmpty() || uri == "none"_L1) {
993 if (bd && bd->bi)
994 bd->bi->pixmap = QPixmap();
995 } else {
996 if (!bd)
997 bd = new QStyleSheetBorderData;
998 if (!bd->bi)
999 bd->bi = new QStyleSheetBorderImageData;
1000
1001 QStyleSheetBorderImageData *bi = bd->bi;
1002 bi->pixmap = QStyleSheetStyle::loadPixmap(fileName: uri, context: object);
1003 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
1004 bi->cuts[i] = cuts[i];
1005 bi->horizStretch = horizStretch;
1006 bi->vertStretch = vertStretch;
1007 }
1008 } else if (decl.d->propertyId == QtBackgroundRole) {
1009 if (bg && bg->brush.style() != Qt::NoBrush)
1010 continue;
1011 int role = decl.d->values.at(i: 0).variant.toInt();
1012 if (role >= Value_FirstColorRole && role <= Value_LastColorRole)
1013 defaultBackground = palette.color(cr: (QPalette::ColorRole)(role-Value_FirstColorRole));
1014 } else if (decl.d->property.startsWith(s: "qproperty-"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)) {
1015 // intentionally left blank...
1016 } else if (decl.d->propertyId == UnknownProperty) {
1017 bool knownStyleHint = false;
1018 for (int i = 0; i < numKnownStyleHints; i++) {
1019 QLatin1StringView styleHint(knownStyleHints[i]);
1020 if (decl.d->property.compare(other: styleHint) == 0) {
1021 QString hintName = QString(styleHint);
1022 QVariant hintValue;
1023 if (hintName.endsWith(s: "alignment"_L1)) {
1024 hintValue = (int) decl.alignmentValue();
1025 } else if (hintName.endsWith(s: "color"_L1)) {
1026 hintValue = (int) decl.colorValue().rgba();
1027 } else if (hintName.endsWith(s: "size"_L1)) {
1028 // Check only for the 'em' case
1029 const QString valueString = decl.d->values.at(i: 0).variant.toString();
1030 const bool isEmSize = valueString.endsWith(s: u"em", cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive);
1031 if (isEmSize || valueString.endsWith(s: u"ex", cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive)) {
1032 // 1em == size of font; 1ex == xHeight of font
1033 // See lengthValueFromData helper in qcssparser.cpp
1034 QFont fontForSize(font);
1035 // if no font is specified, then use the widget font if possible
1036 if (const QWidget *widget; !hasFont && (widget = qobject_cast<const QWidget*>(o: object)))
1037 fontForSize = widget->font();
1038
1039 const QFontMetrics fontMetrics(fontForSize);
1040 qreal pixelSize = isEmSize ? fontMetrics.height() : fontMetrics.xHeight();
1041
1042 // Transform size according to the 'em'/'ex' value
1043 qreal emexSize = {};
1044 if (decl.realValue(r: &emexSize, unit: isEmSize ? "em" : "ex") && emexSize > 0) {
1045 pixelSize *= emexSize;
1046 const QSizeF newSize(pixelSize, pixelSize);
1047 decl.d->parsed = QVariant::fromValue<QSizeF>(value: newSize);
1048 hintValue = newSize;
1049 } else {
1050 qWarning(msg: "Invalid '%s' size for %s. Skipping.",
1051 isEmSize ? "em" : "ex", qPrintable(valueString));
1052 }
1053 } else {
1054 // Normal case where we receive a 'px' or 'pt' unit
1055 hintValue = decl.sizeValue();
1056 }
1057 } else if (hintName.endsWith(s: "icon"_L1)) {
1058 hintValue = decl.iconValue();
1059 } else if (hintName == "button-layout"_L1
1060 && decl.d->values.size() != 0 && decl.d->values.at(i: 0).type == Value::String) {
1061 hintValue = subControlLayout(layout: decl.d->values.at(i: 0).variant.toString());
1062 } else {
1063 int integer;
1064 decl.intValue(i: &integer);
1065 hintValue = integer;
1066 }
1067 styleHints[decl.d->property] = hintValue;
1068 knownStyleHint = true;
1069 break;
1070 }
1071 }
1072 if (!knownStyleHint)
1073 qWarning(msg: "Unknown property %s", qPrintable(decl.d->property));
1074 }
1075 }
1076
1077 if (hasBorder()) {
1078 if (const QWidget *widget = qobject_cast<const QWidget *>(o: object)) {
1079 QStyleSheetStyle *style = const_cast<QStyleSheetStyle *>(globalStyleSheetStyle);
1080 if (!style)
1081 style = qt_styleSheet(style: widget->style());
1082 if (style)
1083 fixupBorder(style->nativeFrameWidth(widget));
1084 }
1085 if (border()->hasBorderImage())
1086 defaultBackground = QBrush();
1087 }
1088}

1153void QRenderRule::fixupBorder(int nativeWidth)
1154{
1155 if (bd == nullptr)
1156 return;
1157
1158 if (!bd->hasBorderImage() || bd->bi->pixmap.isNull()) {
1159 bd->bi = nullptr;
1160 // ignore the color, border of edges that have none border-style
1161 QBrush color = pal ? pal->foreground : QBrush();
1162 const bool hasRadius = bd->radii[0].isValid() || bd->radii[1].isValid()
1163 || bd->radii[2].isValid() || bd->radii[3].isValid();
1164 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
1165 if ((bd->styles[i] == BorderStyle_Native) && hasRadius)
1166 bd->styles[i] = BorderStyle_None;
1167
1168 switch (bd->styles[i]) {
1169 case BorderStyle_None:
1170 // border-style: none forces width to be 0
1171 bd->colors[i] = QBrush();
1172 bd->borders[i] = 0;
1173 break;
1174 case BorderStyle_Native:
1175 if (bd->borders[i] == 0)
1176 bd->borders[i] = nativeWidth;
1177 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
1178 default:
1179 if (bd->colors[i].style() == Qt::NoBrush) // auto-acquire 'color'
1180 bd->colors[i] = color;
1181 break;
1182 }
1183 }
1184
1185 return;
1186 }
1187
1188 // inspect the border image
1189 QStyleSheetBorderImageData *bi = bd->bi;
1190 if (bi->cuts[0] == -1) {
1191 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) // assume, cut = border
1192 bi->cuts[i] = int(border()->borders[i]);
1193 }
1194}
1195
1196void QRenderRule::drawBorderImage(QPainter *p, const QRect& rect)
1197{
1198 setClip(p, rect);
1199 static const Qt::TileRule tileMode2TileRule[] = {
1200 Qt::StretchTile, Qt::RoundTile, Qt::StretchTile, Qt::RepeatTile, Qt::StretchTile };
1201
1202 const QStyleSheetBorderImageData *borderImageData = border()->borderImage();
1203 const int *targetBorders = border()->borders;
1204 const int *sourceBorders = borderImageData->cuts;
1205 QMargins sourceMargins(sourceBorders[LeftEdge], sourceBorders[TopEdge],
1206 sourceBorders[RightEdge], sourceBorders[BottomEdge]);
1207 QMargins targetMargins(targetBorders[LeftEdge], targetBorders[TopEdge],
1208 targetBorders[RightEdge], targetBorders[BottomEdge]);
1209
1210 bool wasSmoothPixmapTransform = p->renderHints() & QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform;
1211 p->setRenderHint(hint: QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform);
1212 qDrawBorderPixmap(painter: p, targetRect: rect, targetMargins, pixmap: borderImageData->pixmap,
1213 sourceRect: QRect(QPoint(), borderImageData->pixmap.size()), sourceMargins,
1214 rules: QTileRules(tileMode2TileRule[borderImageData->horizStretch], tileMode2TileRule[borderImageData->vertStretch]));
1215 p->setRenderHint(hint: QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform, on: wasSmoothPixmapTransform);
1216 unsetClip(p);
1217}

1234void QRenderRule::drawBackgroundImage(QPainter *p, const QRect &rect, QPoint off)
1235{
1236 if (!hasBackground())
1237 return;
1238
1239 const QPixmap& bgp = background()->pixmap;
1240 if (bgp.isNull())
1241 return;
1242
1243 setClip(p, rect: borderRect(r: rect));
1244
1245 if (background()->origin != background()->clip) {
1246 p->save();
1247 p->setClipRect(originRect(rect, origin: background()->clip), op: Qt::IntersectClip);
1248 }
1249
1250 if (background()->attachment == Attachment_Fixed)
1251 off = QPoint(0, 0);
1252
1253 QSize bgpSize = bgp.size() / bgp.devicePixelRatio();
1254 int bgpHeight = bgpSize.height();
1255 int bgpWidth = bgpSize.width();
1256 QRect r = originRect(rect, origin: background()->origin);
1257 QRect aligned = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: Qt::LeftToRight, alignment: background()->position, size: bgpSize, rectangle: r);
1258 QRect inter = aligned.translated(p: -off).intersected(other: r);
1259
1260 switch (background()->repeat) {
1261 case Repeat_Y:
1262 p->drawTiledPixmap(x: inter.x(), y: r.y(), w: inter.width(), h: r.height(), pm: bgp,
1263 sx: inter.x() - aligned.x() + off.x(),
1264 sy: bgpHeight - int(aligned.y() - r.y()) % bgpHeight + off.y());
1265 break;
1266 case Repeat_X:
1267 p->drawTiledPixmap(x: r.x(), y: inter.y(), w: r.width(), h: inter.height(), pm: bgp,
1268 sx: bgpWidth - int(aligned.x() - r.x())%bgpWidth + off.x(),
1269 sy: inter.y() - aligned.y() + off.y());
1270 break;
1271 case Repeat_XY:
1272 p->drawTiledPixmap(rect: r, pm: bgp,
1273 offset: QPoint(bgpWidth - int(aligned.x() - r.x())% bgpWidth + off.x(),
1274 bgpHeight - int(aligned.y() - r.y())%bgpHeight + off.y()));
1275 break;
1276 case Repeat_None:
1277 default:
1278 p->drawPixmap(x: inter.x(), y: inter.y(), pm: bgp, sx: inter.x() - aligned.x() + off.x(),
1279 sy: inter.y() - aligned.y() + off.y(), sw: bgp.width() , sh: bgp.height());
1280 break;
1281 }
1282
1283
1284 if (background()->origin != background()->clip)
1285 p->restore();
1286
1287 unsetClip(p);
1288}

1317QPainterPath QRenderRule::borderClip(QRect r)
1318{
1319 if (!hasBorder())
1320 return QPainterPath();
1321
1322 QSize tlr, trr, blr, brr;
1323 qNormalizeRadii(br: r, radii: bd->radii, tlr: &tlr, trr: &trr, blr: &blr, brr: &brr);
1324 if (tlr.isNull() && trr.isNull() && blr.isNull() && brr.isNull())
1325 return QPainterPath();
1326
1327 const QRectF rect(r);
1328 const int *borders = border()->borders;
1329 QPainterPath path;
1330 qreal curY = rect.y() + borders[TopEdge]/2.0;
1331 path.moveTo(x: rect.x() + tlr.width(), y: curY);
1332 path.lineTo(x: rect.right() - trr.width(), y: curY);
1333 qreal curX = rect.right() - borders[RightEdge]/2.0;
1334 path.arcTo(x: curX - 2*trr.width() + borders[RightEdge], y: curY,
1335 w: trr.width()*2 - borders[RightEdge], h: trr.height()*2 - borders[TopEdge], startAngle: 90, arcLength: -90);
1336
1337 path.lineTo(x: curX, y: rect.bottom() - brr.height());
1338 curY = rect.bottom() - borders[BottomEdge]/2.0;
1339 path.arcTo(x: curX - 2*brr.width() + borders[RightEdge], y: curY - 2*brr.height() + borders[BottomEdge],
1340 w: brr.width()*2 - borders[RightEdge], h: brr.height()*2 - borders[BottomEdge], startAngle: 0, arcLength: -90);
1341
1342 path.lineTo(x: rect.x() + blr.width(), y: curY);
1343 curX = rect.left() + borders[LeftEdge]/2.0;
1344 path.arcTo(x: curX, y: rect.bottom() - 2*blr.height() + borders[BottomEdge]/2.0,
1345 w: blr.width()*2 - borders[LeftEdge], h: blr.height()*2 - borders[BottomEdge], startAngle: 270, arcLength: -90);
1346
1347 path.lineTo(x: curX, y: rect.top() + tlr.height());
1348 path.arcTo(x: curX, y: rect.top() + borders[TopEdge]/2.0,
1349 w: tlr.width()*2 - borders[LeftEdge], h: tlr.height()*2 - borders[TopEdge], startAngle: 180, arcLength: -90);
1350
1351 path.closeSubpath();
1352 return path;
1353}

1377void QRenderRule::drawBackground(QPainter *p, const QRect& rect, const QPoint& off)
1378{
1379 QBrush brush = hasBackground() ? background()->brush : QBrush();
1380 if (brush.style() == Qt::NoBrush)
1381 brush = defaultBackground;
1382
1383 if (brush.style() != Qt::NoBrush) {
1384 Origin origin = hasBackground() ? background()->clip : Origin_Border;
1385 // ### fix for gradients
1386 const QPainterPath &borderPath = borderClip(r: originRect(rect, origin));
1387 if (!borderPath.isEmpty()) {
1388 // Drawn instead of being used as clipping path for better visual quality
1389 bool wasAntialiased = p->renderHints() & QPainter::Antialiasing;
1390 p->setRenderHint(hint: QPainter::Antialiasing);
1391 p->fillPath(path: borderPath, brush);
1392 p->setRenderHint(hint: QPainter::Antialiasing, on: wasAntialiased);
1393 } else {
1394 p->fillRect(originRect(rect, origin), brush);
1395 }
1396 }
1397
1398 drawBackgroundImage(p, rect, off);
1399}

1525class QStyleSheetStyleSelector : public StyleSelector
1526{
1527public:
1528 QStyleSheetStyleSelector() { }
1529
1530 QStringList nodeNames(NodePtr node) const override
1531 {
1532 if (isNullNode(node))
1533 return QStringList();
1534 const QMetaObject *metaObject = OBJECT_PTR(node)->metaObject();
1535#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
1536 if (qstrcmp(str1: metaObject->className(), str2: "QTipLabel") == 0)
1537 return QStringList("QToolTip"_L1);
1538#endif
1539 QStringList result;
1540 do {
1541 result += QString::fromLatin1(ba: metaObject->className()).replace(before: u':', after: u'-');
1542 metaObject = metaObject->superClass();
1543 } while (metaObject != nullptr);
1544 return result;
1545 }
1546 QString attributeValue(NodePtr node, const QCss::AttributeSelector& aSelector) const override
1547 {
1548 if (isNullNode(node))
1549 return QString();
1550
1551 const QString &name = aSelector.name;
1552 QHash<QString, QString> &cache = m_attributeCache[OBJECT_PTR(node)];
1553 QHash<QString, QString>::const_iterator cacheIt = cache.constFind(key: name);
1554 if (cacheIt != cache.constEnd())
1555 return cacheIt.value();
1556
1557 QVariant value;
1558 QString valueStr;
1559 QObject *obj = OBJECT_PTR(node);
1560 const int propertyIndex = obj->metaObject()->indexOfProperty(name: name.toLatin1());
1561 if (propertyIndex == -1) {
1562 value = obj->property(name: name.toLatin1()); // might be a dynamic property
1563 if (!value.isValid()) {
1564 if (name == "class"_L1) {
1565 QString className = QString::fromLatin1(ba: obj->metaObject()->className());
1566 if (className.contains(c: u':'))
1567 className.replace(before: u':', after: u'-');
1568 valueStr = className;
1569 } else if (name == "style"_L1) {
1570 QWidget *w = qobject_cast<QWidget *>(o: obj);
1571 QStyleSheetStyle *proxy = w ? qt_styleSheet(style: w->style()) : nullptr;
1572 if (proxy)
1573 valueStr = QString::fromLatin1(ba: proxy->baseStyle()->metaObject()->className());
1574 }
1575 }
1576 } else {
1577 const QMetaProperty property = obj->metaObject()->property(index: propertyIndex);
1578 value = property.read(obj);
1579 // support Qt 5 selector syntax, which required the integer enum value
1580 if (property.isEnumType()) {
1581 bool isNumber;
1582 aSelector.value.toInt(ok: &isNumber);
1583 if (isNumber)
1584 value.convert(type: QMetaType::fromType<int>());
1585 }
1586 }
1587 if (value.isValid()) {
1588 valueStr = (value.userType() == QMetaType::QStringList
1589 || value.userType() == QMetaType::QVariantList)
1590 ? value.toStringList().join(sep: u' ')
1591 : value.toString();
1592 }
1593 cache[name] = valueStr;
1594 return valueStr;
1595 }
1596 bool nodeNameEquals(NodePtr node, const QString& nodeName) const override
1597 {
1598 if (isNullNode(node))
1599 return false;
1600 const QMetaObject *metaObject = OBJECT_PTR(node)->metaObject();
1601#if QT_CONFIG(tooltip)
1602 if (qstrcmp(str1: metaObject->className(), str2: "QTipLabel") == 0)
1603 return nodeName == "QToolTip"_L1;
1604#endif
1605 do {
1606 const ushort *uc = (const ushort *)nodeName.constData();
1607 const ushort *e = uc + nodeName.size();
1608 const uchar *c = (const uchar *)metaObject->className();
1609 while (*c && uc != e && (*uc == *c || (*c == ':' && *uc == '-'))) {
1610 ++uc;
1611 ++c;
1612 }
1613 if (uc == e && !*c)
1614 return true;
1615 metaObject = metaObject->superClass();
1616 } while (metaObject != nullptr);
1617 return false;
1618 }
1619 bool hasAttributes(NodePtr) const override
1620 { return true; }
1621 QStringList nodeIds(NodePtr node) const override
1622 { return isNullNode(node) ? QStringList() : QStringList(OBJECT_PTR(node)->objectName()); }
1623 bool isNullNode(NodePtr node) const override
1624 { return node.ptr == nullptr; }
1625 NodePtr parentNode(NodePtr node) const override
1626 { NodePtr n; n.ptr = isNullNode(node) ? nullptr : parentObject(OBJECT_PTR(node)); return n; }
1627 NodePtr previousSiblingNode(NodePtr) const override
1628 { NodePtr n; n.ptr = nullptr; return n; }
1629 NodePtr duplicateNode(NodePtr node) const override
1630 { return node; }
1631 void freeNode(NodePtr) const override
1632 { }
1633
1634private:
1635 mutable QHash<const QObject *, QHash<QString, QString> > m_attributeCache;
1636};
1637
1638QList<QCss::StyleRule> QStyleSheetStyle::styleRules(const QObject *obj) const
1639{
1640 QHash<const QObject *, QList<StyleRule>>::const_iterator cacheIt =
1641 styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.constFind(key: obj);
1642 if (cacheIt != styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.constEnd())
1643 return cacheIt.value();
1644
1645 if (!initObject(obj)) {
1646 return QList<StyleRule>();
1647 }
1648
1649 QStyleSheetStyleSelector styleSelector;
1650
1651 StyleSheet defaultSs;
1652 QHash<const void *, StyleSheet>::const_iterator defaultCacheIt = styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.constFind(key: baseStyle());
1653 if (defaultCacheIt == styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.constEnd()) {
1654 defaultSs = getDefaultStyleSheet();
1655 QStyle *bs = baseStyle();
1656 styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.insert(key: bs, value: defaultSs);
1657 QObject::connect(sender: bs, SIGNAL(destroyed(QObject*)), receiver: styleSheetCaches, SLOT(styleDestroyed(QObject*)), Qt::UniqueConnection);
1658 } else {
1659 defaultSs = defaultCacheIt.value();
1660 }
1661 styleSelector.styleSheets += defaultSs;
1662
1663 if (!qApp->styleSheet().isEmpty()) {
1664 StyleSheet appSs;
1665 QHash<const void *, StyleSheet>::const_iterator appCacheIt = styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.constFind(qApp);
1666 if (appCacheIt == styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.constEnd()) {
1667 QString ss = qApp->styleSheet();
1668 if (ss.startsWith(s: "file:///"_L1))
1669 ss.remove(i: 0, len: 8);
1670 parser.init(css: ss, qApp->styleSheet() != ss);
1671 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!parser.parse(&appSs)))
1672 qWarning(msg: "Could not parse application stylesheet");
1673 appSs.origin = StyleSheetOrigin_Inline;
1674 appSs.depth = 1;
1675 styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.insert(qApp, value: appSs);
1676 } else {
1677 appSs = appCacheIt.value();
1678 }
1679 styleSelector.styleSheets += appSs;
1680 }
1681
1682 QList<QCss::StyleSheet> objectSs;
1683 for (const QObject *o = obj; o; o = parentObject(obj: o)) {
1684 QString styleSheet = o->property(name: "styleSheet").toString();
1685 if (styleSheet.isEmpty())
1686 continue;
1687 StyleSheet ss;
1688 QHash<const void *, StyleSheet>::const_iterator objCacheIt = styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.constFind(key: o);
1689 if (objCacheIt == styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.constEnd()) {
1690 parser.init(css: styleSheet);
1691 if (!parser.parse(styleSheet: &ss)) {
1692 parser.init(css: "* {"_L1 + styleSheet + u'}');
1693 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!parser.parse(&ss)))
1694 qWarning() << "Could not parse stylesheet of object" << o;
1695 }
1696 ss.origin = StyleSheetOrigin_Inline;
1697 styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.insert(key: o, value: ss);
1698 } else {
1699 ss = objCacheIt.value();
1700 }
1701 objectSs.append(t: ss);
1702 }
1703
1704 for (int i = 0; i < objectSs.size(); i++)
1705 objectSs[i].depth = objectSs.size() - i + 2;
1706
1707 styleSelector.styleSheets += objectSs;
1708
1709 StyleSelector::NodePtr n;
1710 n.ptr = const_cast<QObject *>(obj);
1711 QList<QCss::StyleRule> rules = styleSelector.styleRulesForNode(node: n);
1712 styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.insert(key: obj, value: rules);
1713 return rules;
1714}

1716/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1717// Rendering rules
1718static QList<Declaration> declarations(const QList<StyleRule> &styleRules, const QString &part,
1719 quint64 pseudoClass = PseudoClass_Unspecified)
1720{
1721 QList<Declaration> decls;
1722 for (int i = 0; i < styleRules.size(); i++) {
1723 const Selector& selector = styleRules.at(i).selectors.at(i: 0);
1724 // Rules with pseudo elements don't cascade. This is an intentional
1725 // diversion for CSS
1726 if (part.compare(s: selector.pseudoElement(), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) != 0)
1727 continue;
1728 quint64 negated = 0;
1729 quint64 cssClass = selector.pseudoClass(negated: &negated);
1730 if ((pseudoClass == PseudoClass_Any) || (cssClass == PseudoClass_Unspecified)
1731 || ((((cssClass & pseudoClass) == cssClass)) && ((negated & pseudoClass) == 0)))
1732 decls += styleRules.at(i).declarations;
1733 }
1734 return decls;
1735}
1736
1737int QStyleSheetStyle::nativeFrameWidth(const QWidget *w)
1738{
1739 QStyle *base = baseStyle();

1773static quint64 pseudoClass(QStyle::State state)
1774{
1775 quint64 pc = 0;
1776 if (state & QStyle::State_Enabled) {
1777 pc |= PseudoClass_Enabled;
1778 if (state & QStyle::State_MouseOver)
1779 pc |= PseudoClass_Hover;
1780 } else {
1781 pc |= PseudoClass_Disabled;
1782 }
1783 if (state & QStyle::State_Active)
1784 pc |= PseudoClass_Active;
1785 if (state & QStyle::State_Window)
1786 pc |= PseudoClass_Window;
1787 if (state & QStyle::State_Sunken)
1788 pc |= PseudoClass_Pressed;
1789 if (state & QStyle::State_HasFocus)
1790 pc |= PseudoClass_Focus;
1791 if (state & QStyle::State_On)
1792 pc |= (PseudoClass_On | PseudoClass_Checked);
1793 if (state & QStyle::State_Off)
1794 pc |= (PseudoClass_Off | PseudoClass_Unchecked);
1795 if (state & QStyle::State_NoChange)
1796 pc |= PseudoClass_Indeterminate;
1797 if (state & QStyle::State_Selected)
1798 pc |= PseudoClass_Selected;
1799 if (state & QStyle::State_Horizontal)
1800 pc |= PseudoClass_Horizontal;
1801 else
1802 pc |= PseudoClass_Vertical;
1803 if (state & (QStyle::State_Open | QStyle::State_On | QStyle::State_Sunken))
1804 pc |= PseudoClass_Open;
1805 else
1806 pc |= PseudoClass_Closed;
1807 if (state & QStyle::State_Children)
1808 pc |= PseudoClass_Children;
1809 if (state & QStyle::State_Sibling)
1810 pc |= PseudoClass_Sibling;
1811 if (state & QStyle::State_ReadOnly)
1812 pc |= PseudoClass_ReadOnly;
1813 if (state & QStyle::State_Item)
1814 pc |= PseudoClass_Item;
1815#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
1816 if (state & QStyle::State_HasEditFocus)
1817 pc |= PseudoClass_EditFocus;
1818#endif
1819 return pc;
1820}

1839QRenderRule QStyleSheetStyle::renderRule(const QObject *obj, int element, quint64 state) const
1840{
1841 qt_check_if_internal_object(obj: &obj, element: &element);
1842 QHash<quint64, QRenderRule> &cache = styleSheetCaches->renderRulesCache[obj][element];
1843 QHash<quint64, QRenderRule>::const_iterator cacheIt = cache.constFind(key: state);
1844 if (cacheIt != cache.constEnd())
1845 return cacheIt.value();
1846
1847 if (!initObject(obj))
1848 return QRenderRule();
1849
1850 quint64 stateMask = 0;
1851 const QList<StyleRule> rules = styleRules(obj);
1852 for (int i = 0; i < rules.size(); i++) {
1853 const Selector& selector = rules.at(i).selectors.at(i: 0);
1854 quint64 negated = 0;
1855 stateMask |= selector.pseudoClass(negated: &negated);
1856 stateMask |= negated;
1857 }
1858
1859 cacheIt = cache.constFind(key: state & stateMask);
1860 if (cacheIt != cache.constEnd()) {
1861 QRenderRule newRule = cacheIt.value();
1862 cache[state] = newRule;
1863 return newRule;
1864 }
1865
1866
1867 const QString part = QLatin1StringView(knownPseudoElements[element].name);
1868 QList<Declaration> decls = declarations(styleRules: rules, part, pseudoClass: state);
1869 QRenderRule newRule(decls, obj);
1870 cache[state] = newRule;
1871 if ((state & stateMask) != state)
1872 cache[state&stateMask] = newRule;
1873 return newRule;
1874}

2156bool QStyleSheetStyle::hasStyleRule(const QObject *obj, int part) const
2157{
2158 QHash<int, bool> &cache = styleSheetCaches->hasStyleRuleCache[obj];
2159 QHash<int, bool>::const_iterator cacheIt = cache.constFind(key: part);
2160 if (cacheIt != cache.constEnd())
2161 return cacheIt.value();
2162
2163 if (!initObject(obj))
2164 return false;
2165
2166 const QList<StyleRule> &rules = styleRules(obj);
2167 if (part == PseudoElement_None) {
2168 bool result = obj && !rules.isEmpty();
2169 cache[part] = result;
2170 return result;
2171 }
2172
2173 auto pseudoElement = QLatin1StringView(knownPseudoElements[part].name);
2174 for (int i = 0; i < rules.size(); i++) {
2175 const Selector& selector = rules.at(i).selectors.at(i: 0);
2176 if (pseudoElement.compare(other: selector.pseudoElement(), cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive) == 0) {
2177 cache[part] = true;
2178 return true;
2179 }
2180 }
2181
2182 cache[part] = false;
2183 return false;
2184}

2335 break;
2336
2337 case PseudoElement_SpinBoxUpButton:
2338 case PseudoElement_SpinBoxDownButton:
2339 if (sz.width() == -1)
2340 sz.setWidth(16);
2341 if (sz.height() == -1)
2342 sz.setHeight(rect.height()/2);
2343 break;
2344
2345 case PseudoElement_ToolButtonMenu:
2346 if (sz.width() == -1)
2347 sz.setWidth(base->pixelMetric(metric: PM_MenuButtonIndicator, option: nullptr, widget: w));
2348 break;
2349
2350 case PseudoElement_HeaderViewUpArrow:
2351 case PseudoElement_HeaderViewDownArrow: {
2352 int pm = base->pixelMetric(metric: PM_HeaderMargin, option: nullptr, widget: w);
2353 if (sz.width() == -1)
2354 sz.setWidth(pm);
2355 if (sz.height() == 1)
2356 sz.setHeight(pm);
2357 break;
2358 }
2359
2360 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarFirst:
2361 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarLast:
2362 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarAddLine:
2363 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarSubLine:
2364 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider: {
2365 int pm = pixelMetric(metric: QStyle::PM_ScrollBarExtent, option: nullptr, widget: w);
2366 if (sz.width() == -1)
2367 sz.setWidth(pm);
2368 if (sz.height() == -1)
2369 sz.setHeight(pm);
2370 break;
2371 }
2372
2373 case PseudoElement_DockWidgetCloseButton:
2374 case PseudoElement_DockWidgetFloatButton: {
2375 int iconSize = pixelMetric(metric: PM_SmallIconSize, option: nullptr, widget: w);
2376 return QSize(iconSize, iconSize);
2377 }
2378
2379 default:
2380 break;
2381 }
2382
2383 // expand to rectangle
2384 if (sz.height() == -1)
2385 sz.setHeight(rect.height());
2386 if (sz.width() == -1)
2387 sz.setWidth(rect.width());
2388
2389 return sz;
2390}

2392static PositionMode defaultPositionMode(int pe)
2393{
2394 switch (pe) {
2395 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarFirst:
2396 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarLast:
2397 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarAddLine:
2398 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarSubLine:
2399 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarAddPage:
2400 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarSubPage:
2401 case PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider:
2402 case PseudoElement_SliderGroove:
2403 case PseudoElement_SliderHandle:
2404 case PseudoElement_TabWidgetPane:
2405 return PositionMode_Absolute;
2406 default:
2407 return PositionMode_Static;
2408 }
2409}
2410
2411QRect QStyleSheetStyle::positionRect(const QWidget *w, const QRenderRule &rule2, int pe,
2412 const QRect &originRect, Qt::LayoutDirection dir) const
2413{
2414 const QStyleSheetPositionData *p = rule2.position();
2415 PositionMode mode = (p && p->mode != PositionMode_Unknown) ? p->mode : defaultPositionMode(pe);
2416 Qt::Alignment position = (p && p->position != 0) ? p->position : defaultPosition(pe);
2417 QRect r;
2418
2419 if (mode != PositionMode_Absolute) {
2420 QSize sz = defaultSize(w, sz: rule2.size(), rect: originRect, pe);
2421 sz = sz.expandedTo(otherSize: rule2.minimumContentsSize());
2422 r = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: dir, alignment: position, size: sz, rectangle: originRect);
2423 if (p) {
2424 int left = p->left ? p->left : -p->right;
2425 int top = p->top ? p->top : -p->bottom;
2426 r.translate(dx: dir == Qt::LeftToRight ? left : -left, dy: top);
2427 }
2428 } else {
2429 r = p ? originRect.adjusted(xp1: dir == Qt::LeftToRight ? p->left : p->right, yp1: p->top,
2430 xp2: dir == Qt::LeftToRight ? -p->right : -p->left, yp2: -p->bottom)
2431 : originRect;
2432 if (rule2.hasContentsSize()) {
2433 QSize sz = rule2.size().expandedTo(otherSize: rule2.minimumContentsSize());
2434 if (sz.width() == -1) sz.setWidth(r.width());
2435 if (sz.height() == -1) sz.setHeight(r.height());
2436 r = QStyle::alignedRect(direction: dir, alignment: position, size: sz, rectangle: r);
2437 }
2438 }
2439 return r;
2440}
2441
2442QRect QStyleSheetStyle::positionRect(const QWidget *w, const QRenderRule& rule1, const QRenderRule& rule2, int pe,
2443 const QRect& rect, Qt::LayoutDirection dir) const
2444{
2445 const QStyleSheetPositionData *p = rule2.position();
2446 Origin origin = (p && p->origin != Origin_Unknown) ? p->origin : defaultOrigin(pe);
2447 QRect originRect = rule1.originRect(rect, origin);
2448 return positionRect(w, rule2, pe, originRect, dir);
2449}

2549static quint64 extendedPseudoClass(const QWidget *w)
2550{
2551 quint64 pc = w->isWindow() ? quint64(PseudoClass_Window) : 0;
2552#if QT_CONFIG(abstractslider)
2553 if (const QAbstractSlider *slider = qobject_cast<const QAbstractSlider *>(object: w)) {
2554 pc |= ((slider->orientation() == Qt::Vertical) ? PseudoClass_Vertical : PseudoClass_Horizontal);
2555 } else
2556#endif
2557#if QT_CONFIG(combobox)
2558 if (const QComboBox *combo = qobject_cast<const QComboBox *>(object: w)) {
2559 if (combo->isEditable())
2560 pc |= (combo->isEditable() ? PseudoClass_Editable : PseudoClass_ReadOnly);
2561 } else
2562#endif
2563#if QT_CONFIG(lineedit)
2564 if (const QLineEdit *edit = qobject_cast<const QLineEdit *>(object: w)) {
2565 pc |= (edit->isReadOnly() ? PseudoClass_ReadOnly : PseudoClass_Editable);
2566 } else
2567#endif
2568#if QT_CONFIG(textedit)
2569 if (const QTextEdit *edit = qobject_cast<const QTextEdit *>(object: w)) {
2570 pc |= (edit->isReadOnly() ? PseudoClass_ReadOnly : PseudoClass_Editable);
2571 } else
2572 if (const QPlainTextEdit *edit = qobject_cast<const QPlainTextEdit *>(object: w)) {
2573 pc |= (edit->isReadOnly() ? PseudoClass_ReadOnly : PseudoClass_Editable);
2574 } else
2575#endif
2576 {}
2577 return pc;
2578}

2580// sets up the geometry of the widget. We set a dynamic property when
2581// we modify the min/max size of the widget. The min/max size is restored
2582// to their original value when a new stylesheet that does not contain
2583// the CSS properties is set and when the widget has this dynamic property set.
2584// This way we don't trample on users who had setup a min/max size in code and
2585// don't use stylesheets at all.
2586void QStyleSheetStyle::setGeometry(QWidget *w)
2587{
2588 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, element: PseudoElement_None, state: PseudoClass_Enabled | extendedPseudoClass(w));
2589 const QStyleSheetGeometryData *geo = rule.geometry();
2590 if (w->property(name: "_q_stylesheet_minw").toBool()
2591 && ((!rule.hasGeometry() || geo->minWidth == -1))) {
2592 w->setMinimumWidth(0);
2593 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_minw", value: QVariant());
2594 }
2595 if (w->property(name: "_q_stylesheet_minh").toBool()
2596 && ((!rule.hasGeometry() || geo->minHeight == -1))) {
2597 w->setMinimumHeight(0);
2598 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_minh", value: QVariant());
2599 }
2600 if (w->property(name: "_q_stylesheet_maxw").toBool()
2601 && ((!rule.hasGeometry() || geo->maxWidth == -1))) {
2602 w->setMaximumWidth(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX);
2603 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_maxw", value: QVariant());
2604 }
2605 if (w->property(name: "_q_stylesheet_maxh").toBool()
2606 && ((!rule.hasGeometry() || geo->maxHeight == -1))) {
2607 w->setMaximumHeight(QWIDGETSIZE_MAX);
2608 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_maxh", value: QVariant());
2609 }
2610
2611
2612 if (rule.hasGeometry()) {
2613 if (geo->minWidth != -1) {
2614 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_minw", value: true);
2615 w->setMinimumWidth(rule.boxSize(cs: QSize(qMax(a: geo->width, b: geo->minWidth), 0)).width());
2616 }
2617 if (geo->minHeight != -1) {
2618 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_minh", value: true);
2619 w->setMinimumHeight(rule.boxSize(cs: QSize(0, qMax(a: geo->height, b: geo->minHeight))).height());
2620 }
2621 if (geo->maxWidth != -1) {
2622 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_maxw", value: true);
2623 w->setMaximumWidth(rule.boxSize(cs: QSize(qMin(a: geo->width == -1 ? QWIDGETSIZE_MAX : geo->width,
2624 b: geo->maxWidth == -1 ? QWIDGETSIZE_MAX : geo->maxWidth), 0)).width());
2625 }
2626 if (geo->maxHeight != -1) {
2627 w->setProperty(name: "_q_stylesheet_maxh", value: true);
2628 w->setMaximumHeight(rule.boxSize(cs: QSize(0, qMin(a: geo->height == -1 ? QWIDGETSIZE_MAX : geo->height,
2629 b: geo->maxHeight == -1 ? QWIDGETSIZE_MAX : geo->maxHeight))).height());
2630 }
2631 }
2632}
2633
2634void QStyleSheetStyle::setProperties(QWidget *w)
2635{
2636 // The final occurrence of each property is authoritative.
2637 // Set value for each property in the order of property final occurrence
2638 // since properties interact.
2639
2640 const QList<Declaration> decls = declarations(styleRules: styleRules(obj: w), part: QString());
2641 QList<int> finals; // indices in reverse order of each property's final occurrence
2642
2643 {
2644 // scan decls for final occurrence of each "qproperty"
2645 QDuplicateTracker<QString> propertySet(decls.size());
2646 for (int i = decls.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2647 const QString property = decls.at(i).d->property;
2648 if (!property.startsWith(s: "qproperty-"_L1, cs: Qt::CaseInsensitive))
2649 continue;
2650 if (!propertySet.hasSeen(s: property))
2651 finals.append(t: i);
2652 }
2653 }
2654
2655 for (int i = finals.size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
2656 const Declaration &decl = decls.at(i: finals[i]);
2657 QStringView property = decl.d->property;
2658 property = property.mid(pos: 10); // strip "qproperty-"
2659 const auto propertyL1 = property.toLatin1();
2660
2661 const QMetaObject *metaObject = w->metaObject();
2662 int index = metaObject->indexOfProperty(name: propertyL1);
2663 if (Q_UNLIKELY(index == -1)) {
2664 qWarning() << w << " does not have a property named " << property;
2665 continue;
2666 }
2667 const QMetaProperty metaProperty = metaObject->property(index);
2668 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!metaProperty.isWritable() || !metaProperty.isDesignable())) {
2669 qWarning() << w << " cannot design property named " << property;
2670 continue;
2671 }
2672
2673 QVariant v;
2674 const QVariant value = w->property(name: propertyL1);
2675 switch (value.userType()) {
2676 case QMetaType::QIcon: v = decl.iconValue(); break;
2677 case QMetaType::QImage: v = QImage(decl.uriValue()); break;
2678 case QMetaType::QPixmap: v = QPixmap(decl.uriValue()); break;
2679 case QMetaType::QRect: v = decl.rectValue(); break;
2680 case QMetaType::QSize: v = decl.sizeValue(); break;
2681 case QMetaType::QColor: v = decl.colorValue(); break;
2682 case QMetaType::QBrush: v = decl.brushValue(); break;
2683#ifndef QT_NO_SHORTCUT
2684 case QMetaType::QKeySequence: v = QKeySequence(decl.d->values.at(i: 0).variant.toString()); break;
2685#endif
2686 default: v = decl.d->values.at(i: 0).variant; break;
2687 }
2688
2689 if (propertyL1 == QByteArrayView("styleSheet") && value == v)
2690 continue;
2691
2692 w->setProperty(name: propertyL1, value: v);
2693 }
2694}
2695
2696void QStyleSheetStyle::setPalette(QWidget *w)
2697{
2698 struct RuleRoleMap {
2699 int state;
2700 QPalette::ColorGroup group;
2701 } map[3] = {
2702 { .state: int(PseudoClass_Active | PseudoClass_Enabled), .group: QPalette::Active },
2703 { .state: PseudoClass_Disabled, .group: QPalette::Disabled },
2704 { .state: PseudoClass_Enabled, .group: QPalette::Inactive }
2705 };
2706
2707 const bool useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles =
2708 QCoreApplication::testAttribute(attribute: Qt::AA_UseStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles);
2709
2710 QPalette p;
2711 if (!useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles)
2712 p = w->palette();
2713
2714 QWidget *ew = embeddedWidget(w);
2715
2716 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
2717 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, element: PseudoElement_None, state: map[i].state | extendedPseudoClass(w));
2718 if (i == 0) {
2719 if (!w->property(name: "_q_styleSheetWidgetFont").isValid()) {
2720 saveWidgetFont(w, font: w->d_func()->localFont());
2721 }
2722 updateStyleSheetFont(w);
2723 if (ew != w)
2724 updateStyleSheetFont(w: ew);
2725 }
2726
2727 rule.configurePalette(p: &p, cg: map[i].group, w: ew, embedded: ew != w);
2728 }
2729
2730 if (!useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles || p.resolveMask() != 0) {
2731 QPalette wp = w->palette();
2732 styleSheetCaches->customPaletteWidgets.insert(key: w, value: {.oldWidgetValue: wp, .resolveMask: p.resolveMask()});
2733
2734 if (useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles) {
2735 p = p.resolve(other: wp);
2736 p.setResolveMask(p.resolveMask() | wp.resolveMask());
2737 }
2738
2739 w->setPalette(p);
2740 if (ew != w)
2741 ew->setPalette(p);
2742 }
2743}

2745void QStyleSheetStyle::unsetPalette(QWidget *w)
2746{
2747 const bool useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles =
2748 QCoreApplication::testAttribute(attribute: Qt::AA_UseStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles);
2749
2750 const auto it = styleSheetCaches->customPaletteWidgets.find(key: w);
2751 if (it != styleSheetCaches->customPaletteWidgets.end()) {
2752 auto customizedPalette = std::move(*it);
2753 styleSheetCaches->customPaletteWidgets.erase(it);
2754
2755 QPalette original;
2756 if (useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles)
2757 original = std::move(customizedPalette).reverted(current: w->palette());
2758 else
2759 original = customizedPalette.oldWidgetValue;
2760
2761 w->setPalette(original);
2762 QWidget *ew = embeddedWidget(w);
2763 if (ew != w)
2764 ew->setPalette(original);
2765 }
2766
2767 if (useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles) {
2768 unsetStyleSheetFont(w);
2769 QWidget *ew = embeddedWidget(w);
2770 if (ew != w)
2771 unsetStyleSheetFont(ew);
2772 } else {
2773 QVariant oldFont = w->property(name: "_q_styleSheetWidgetFont");
2774 if (oldFont.isValid()) {
2775 w->setFont(qvariant_cast<QFont>(v: oldFont));
2776 }
2777 }
2778
2779 if (styleSheetCaches->autoFillDisabledWidgets.contains(value: w)) {
2780 embeddedWidget(w)->setAutoFillBackground(true);
2781 styleSheetCaches->autoFillDisabledWidgets.remove(value: w);
2782 }
2783}

2785void QStyleSheetStyle::unsetStyleSheetFont(QWidget *w) const
2786{
2787 const auto it = styleSheetCaches->customFontWidgets.find(key: w);
2788 if (it != styleSheetCaches->customFontWidgets.end()) {
2789 auto customizedFont = std::move(*it);
2790 styleSheetCaches->customFontWidgets.erase(it);
2791 w->setFont(std::move(customizedFont).reverted(current: w->font()));
2792 }

2795static void updateObjects(const QList<const QObject *>& objects)
2796{
2797 if (!styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.isEmpty() || !styleSheetCaches->hasStyleRuleCache.isEmpty() || !styleSheetCaches->renderRulesCache.isEmpty()) {
2798 for (const QObject *object : objects) {
2799 styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.remove(key: object);
2800 styleSheetCaches->hasStyleRuleCache.remove(key: object);
2801 styleSheetCaches->renderRulesCache.remove(key: object);
2802 }
2803 }
2804
2805 QEvent event(QEvent::StyleChange);
2806 for (const QObject *object : objects) {
2807 if (auto widget = qobject_cast<QWidget*>(o: const_cast<QObject*>(object))) {
2808 widget->style()->polish(widget);
2809 QCoreApplication::sendEvent(receiver: widget, event: &event);
2810 QList<const QObject *> children;
2811 children.reserve(size: widget->children().size() + 1);
2812 for (auto child: std::as_const(t: widget->children()))
2813 children.append(t: child);
2814 updateObjects(objects: children);
2815 }
2816 }

2864/*!
2865 * Make sure that the cache will be clean by connecting destroyed if needed.
2866 * return false if the widget is not stylable;
2867 */
2868bool QStyleSheetStyle::initObject(const QObject *obj) const
2869{
2870 if (!obj)
2871 return false;
2872 if (const QWidget *w = qobject_cast<const QWidget*>(o: obj)) {
2873 if (w->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_StyleSheet))
2874 return true;
2875 if (unstylable(w))
2876 return false;
2877 const_cast<QWidget *>(w)->setAttribute(Qt::WA_StyleSheet, on: true);
2878 }
2879
2880 QObject::connect(sender: obj, SIGNAL(destroyed(QObject*)), receiver: styleSheetCaches, SLOT(objectDestroyed(QObject*)), Qt::UniqueConnection);
2881 return true;
2882}
2883
2884void QStyleSheetStyle::polish(QWidget *w)
2885{
2886 baseStyle()->polish(widget: w);
2887 RECURSION_GUARD(return)
2888
2889 if (!initObject(obj: w))
2890 return;
2891
2892 if (styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.contains(key: w)) {
2893 // the widget accessed its style pointer before polish (or repolish)
2894 // (example: the QAbstractSpinBox constructor ask for the stylehint)
2895 styleSheetCaches->styleRulesCache.remove(key: w);
2896 styleSheetCaches->hasStyleRuleCache.remove(key: w);
2897 styleSheetCaches->renderRulesCache.remove(key: w);
2898 styleSheetCaches->styleSheetCache.remove(key: w);
2899 }
2900 setGeometry(w);
2901 setProperties(w);
2902 unsetPalette(w);
2903 setPalette(w);
2904
2905 //set the WA_Hover attribute if one of the selector depends of the hover state
2906 QList<StyleRule> rules = styleRules(obj: w);
2907 for (int i = 0; i < rules.size(); i++) {
2908 const Selector& selector = rules.at(i).selectors.at(i: 0);
2909 quint64 negated = 0;
2910 quint64 cssClass = selector.pseudoClass(negated: &negated);
2911 if ( cssClass & PseudoClass_Hover || negated & PseudoClass_Hover) {
2912 w->setAttribute(Qt::WA_Hover);
2913 embeddedWidget(w)->setAttribute(Qt::WA_Hover);
2914 embeddedWidget(w)->setMouseTracking(true);
2915 }
2916 }
2917
2918
2919#if QT_CONFIG(scrollarea)
2920 if (QAbstractScrollArea *sa = qobject_cast<QAbstractScrollArea *>(object: w)) {
2921 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: sa, element: PseudoElement_None, state: PseudoClass_Enabled);
2922 if ((rule.hasBorder() && rule.border()->hasBorderImage())

3601{
3602 const QIcon::Mode mode = mi->state & QStyle::State_Enabled
3603 ? (mi->state & QStyle::State_Selected ? QIcon::Active : QIcon::Normal)

4426 }
4427 break;
4428
4429 case CE_DockWidgetTitle:

4432 if (!subRule.hasDrawable() && !subRule.hasPosition())
4433 break;
4434 if (subRule.hasDrawable()) {
4435 subRule.drawRule(p, rect: opt->rect);
4436 } else {
4437 QStyleOptionDockWidget dwCopy(*dwOpt);
4438 dwCopy.title = QString();
4439 baseStyle()->drawControl(element: ce, opt: &dwCopy, p, w);
4440 }
4441
4442 if (!dwOpt->title.isEmpty()) {
4443 QRect r = subElementRect(r: SE_DockWidgetTitleBarText, opt, widget: w);
4444 if (dwOpt->verticalTitleBar) {
4445 r = r.transposed();
4446 p->save();
4447 p->translate(dx: r.left(), dy: r.top() + r.width());
4448 p->rotate(a: -90);
4449 p->translate(dx: -r.left(), dy: -r.top());

4451 r = subRule.contentsRect(r);
4452
4453 Qt::Alignment alignment;
4454 if (subRule.hasPosition())
4455 alignment = subRule.position()->textAlignment;
4456 if (alignment == 0)
4457 alignment = Qt::AlignLeft;

4460 drawItemText(painter: p, rect: r,
4461 alignment, pal: dwOpt->palette,

4463 textRole: QPalette::WindowText);

4470 }

4477 frmOpt.rect = rule.borderRect(r: frmOpt.rect);

4479 }
4480 // else, borders are already drawn in PE_Widget
4481 }
4482 return;
4483
4484
4485 default:
4486 break;
4487 }
4488
4489 if (pe1 != PseudoElement_None) {
4490 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: pe1);
4491 if (subRule.bg != nullptr || subRule.hasDrawable()) {
4492 //We test subRule.bg directly because hasBackground() would return false for background:none.
4493 //But we still don't want the default drawning in that case (example for QScrollBar::add-page) (task 198926)
4494 subRule.drawRule(p, rect: opt->rect);
4495 } else if (fallback) {
4496 QWindowsStyle::drawControl(element: ce, opt, p, w);
4497 pe2 = PseudoElement_None;
4498 } else {
4499 baseStyle()->drawControl(element: ce, opt, p, w);
4500 }
4501 if (pe2 != PseudoElement_None) {
4502 QRenderRule subSubRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: pe2);
4503 QRect r = positionRect(w, rule1: subRule, rule2: subSubRule, pe: pe2, rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
4504 subSubRule.drawRule(p, rect: r);

4506 return;
4507 }
4508
4509 baseStyle()->drawControl(element: ce, opt, p, w);

4873QStyle::SubControl QStyleSheetStyle::hitTestComplexControl(ComplexControl cc, const QStyleOptionComplex *opt,
4874 const QPoint &pt, const QWidget *w) const
4875{
4876 RECURSION_GUARD(return baseStyle()->hitTestComplexControl(cc, opt, pt, w))
4877 switch (cc) {
4878 case CC_TitleBar:
4879 if (const QStyleOptionTitleBar *tb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionTitleBar *>(opt)) {
4880 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TitleBar);
4881 if (rule.hasDrawable() || rule.hasBox() || rule.hasBorder()) {
4882 QHash<QStyle::SubControl, QRect> layout = titleBarLayout(w, tb);
4883 QRect r;
4884 QStyle::SubControl sc = QStyle::SC_None;
4885 uint ctrl = SC_TitleBarSysMenu;
4886 while (ctrl <= SC_TitleBarLabel) {
4887 r = layout[QStyle::SubControl(ctrl)];
4888 if (r.isValid() && r.contains(p: pt)) {
4889 sc = QStyle::SubControl(ctrl);
4890 break;
4891 }
4892 ctrl <<= 1;
4893 }
4894 return sc;
4895 }
4896 }
4897 break;
4898
4899 case CC_MdiControls:
4900 if (hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiCloseButton)
4901 || hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiNormalButton)
4902 || hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiMinButton))
4903 return QWindowsStyle::hitTestComplexControl(cc, opt, pt, w);
4904 break;
4905
4906 case CC_ScrollBar: {
4907 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, opt);
4908 if (!rule.hasDrawable() && !rule.hasBox())
4909 break;
4910 }
4911 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
4912 case CC_SpinBox:
4913 case CC_GroupBox:
4914 case CC_ComboBox:
4915 case CC_Slider:
4916 case CC_ToolButton:
4917 return QWindowsStyle::hitTestComplexControl(cc, opt, pt, w);

4937{

4939

4941 QRenderRule subRule;
4942
4943 switch (m) {
4944 case PM_MenuButtonIndicator:
4945#if QT_CONFIG(toolbutton)
4946 // QToolButton adds this directly to the width
4947 if (qobject_cast<const QToolButton *>(object: w)) {
4948 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder())
4949 return 0;
4950 if (const auto *tbOpt = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionToolButton*>(opt)) {
4951 if (tbOpt->features & QStyleOptionToolButton::MenuButtonPopup)
4952 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ToolButtonMenu);
4953 else
4954 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ToolButtonMenuIndicator);

4964 break;

4967 case PM_ButtonShiftVertical:
4968 case PM_ButtonMargin:
4969 case PM_ButtonDefaultIndicator:
4970 if (rule.hasBox())

4972 break;
4973
4974 case PM_DefaultFrameWidth:
4975 if (!rule.hasNativeBorder())

4978
4979 case PM_ExclusiveIndicatorWidth:
4980 case PM_IndicatorWidth:
4981 case PM_ExclusiveIndicatorHeight:

4986 ? subRule.size().width() : subRule.size().height();

4990 case PM_DockWidgetFrameWidth:
4991 case PM_ToolTipLabelFrameWidth: // border + margin + padding (support only one width)
4992 if (!rule.hasDrawable())
4993 break;
4994
4995 return (rule.border() ? rule.border()->borders[LeftEdge] : 0)
4996 + (rule.hasBox() ? rule.box()->margins[LeftEdge] + rule.box()->paddings[LeftEdge]: 0);

4998 case PM_ToolBarFrameWidth:
4999 if (rule.hasBorder() || rule.hasBox())
5000 return (rule.border() ? rule.border()->borders[LeftEdge] : 0)
5001 + (rule.hasBox() ? rule.box()->paddings[LeftEdge]: 0);
5002 break;
5003
5004 case PM_MenuPanelWidth:
5005 case PM_MenuBarPanelWidth:
5006 if (rule.hasBorder() || rule.hasBox())
5007 return (rule.border() ? rule.border()->borders[LeftEdge] : 0)
5008 + (rule.hasBox() ? rule.box()->margins[LeftEdge]: 0);
5009 break;
5010
5011
5012 case PM_MenuHMargin:
5013 case PM_MenuBarHMargin:
5014 if (rule.hasBox())
5015 return rule.box()->paddings[LeftEdge];
5016 break;
5017
5018 case PM_MenuVMargin:
5019 case PM_MenuBarVMargin:
5020 if (rule.hasBox())
5021 return rule.box()->paddings[TopEdge];
5022 break;
5023
5024 case PM_DockWidgetTitleBarButtonMargin:
5025 case PM_ToolBarItemMargin:
5026 if (rule.hasBox())
5027 return rule.box()->margins[TopEdge];
5028 break;
5029
5030 case PM_ToolBarItemSpacing:
5031 case PM_MenuBarItemSpacing:
5032 if (rule.hasBox() && rule.box()->spacing != -1)
5033 return rule.box()->spacing;
5034 break;
5035
5036 case PM_MenuTearoffHeight:
5037 case PM_MenuScrollerHeight: {
5038 PseudoElement ps = m == PM_MenuTearoffHeight ? PseudoElement_MenuTearoff : PseudoElement_MenuScroller;
5039 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: ps);
5040 if (subRule.hasContentsSize())
5041 return subRule.size().height();
5042 break;
5043 }
5044
5045 case PM_ToolBarExtensionExtent:
5046 break;
5047
5048 case PM_SplitterWidth:
5049 case PM_ToolBarSeparatorExtent:
5050 case PM_ToolBarHandleExtent: {
5051 PseudoElement ps;
5052 if (m == PM_ToolBarHandleExtent) ps = PseudoElement_ToolBarHandle;
5053 else if (m == PM_SplitterWidth) ps = PseudoElement_SplitterHandle;
5054 else ps = PseudoElement_ToolBarSeparator;
5055 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: ps);
5056 if (subRule.hasContentsSize()) {
5057 QSize sz = subRule.size();
5058 return (opt && opt->state & QStyle::State_Horizontal) ? sz.width() : sz.height();
5059 }
5060 break;
5061 }
5062
5063 case PM_RadioButtonLabelSpacing:
5064 if (rule.hasBox() && rule.box()->spacing != -1)
5065 return rule.box()->spacing;
5066 break;
5067 case PM_CheckBoxLabelSpacing:
5068#if QT_CONFIG(checkbox)
5069 if (qobject_cast<const QCheckBox *>(object: w)) {
5070 if (rule.hasBox() && rule.box()->spacing != -1)
5071 return rule.box()->spacing;
5072 }
5073#endif
5074 // assume group box
5075 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_GroupBoxTitle);
5076 if (subRule.hasBox() && subRule.box()->spacing != -1)
5077 return subRule.box()->spacing;
5078 break;
5079
5080#if QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
5081 case PM_ScrollBarExtent:
5082 if (rule.hasContentsSize()) {
5083 QSize sz = rule.size();
5084 if (const QStyleOptionSlider *sb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionSlider *>(opt))
5085 return sb->orientation == Qt::Horizontal ? sz.height() : sz.width();
5086 return sz.width() == -1 ? sz.height() : sz.width();
5087 }
5088 break;
5089
5090 case PM_ScrollBarSliderMin:
5091 if (hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider)) {
5092 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider);
5093 QSize msz = subRule.minimumSize();
5094 if (const QStyleOptionSlider *sb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionSlider *>(opt))
5095 return sb->orientation == Qt::Horizontal ? msz.width() : msz.height();
5096 return msz.width() == -1 ? msz.height() : msz.width();
5097 }
5098 break;
5099
5100 case PM_ScrollView_ScrollBarSpacing:
5101 if (!rule.hasNativeBorder() || rule.hasBox())
5102 return 0;
5103 break;
5104
5105 case PM_ScrollView_ScrollBarOverlap:
5106 if (!proxy()->styleHint(stylehint: SH_ScrollBar_Transient, opt, widget: w))
5107 return 0;
5108 break;
5109#endif // QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
5110
5111
5112 case PM_ProgressBarChunkWidth:
5113 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ProgressBarChunk);
5114 if (subRule.hasContentsSize()) {
5115 QSize sz = subRule.size();
5116 return (opt->state & QStyle::State_Horizontal)
5117 ? sz.width() : sz.height();
5118 }
5119 break;
5120
5121#if QT_CONFIG(tabwidget)
5122 case PM_TabBarTabHSpace:
5123 case PM_TabBarTabVSpace:
5124 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TabBarTab);
5125 if (subRule.hasBox() || subRule.hasBorder())
5126 return 0;
5127 break;
5128
5129 case PM_TabBarScrollButtonWidth:
5130 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TabBarScroller);
5131 if (subRule.hasContentsSize()) {
5132 QSize sz = subRule.size();
5133 return (sz.width() != -1 ? sz.width() : sz.height()) / 2;
5134 }
5135 break;
5136
5137 case PM_TabBarTabShiftHorizontal:
5138 case PM_TabBarTabShiftVertical:
5139 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TabBarTab);
5140 if (subRule.hasBox())
5141 return 0;
5142 break;
5143
5144 case PM_TabBarBaseOverlap: {
5145 const QWidget *tabWidget = qobject_cast<const QTabWidget *>(object: w);
5146 if (!tabWidget && w)
5147 tabWidget = w->parentWidget();
5148 if (hasStyleRule(obj: tabWidget, part: PseudoElement_TabWidgetPane)) {
5149 return 0;
5150 }
5151 break;
5152 }
5153#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabwidget)
5154
5155 case PM_SliderThickness: // horizontal slider's height (sizeHint)
5156 case PM_SliderLength: // minimum length of slider
5157 if (rule.hasContentsSize()) {
5158 bool horizontal = opt->state & QStyle::State_Horizontal;
5159 if (m == PM_SliderThickness) {
5160 QSize sz = rule.size();
5161 return horizontal ? sz.height() : sz.width();
5162 } else {
5163 QSize msz = rule.minimumContentsSize();
5164 return horizontal ? msz.width() : msz.height();
5165 }
5166 }
5167 break;
5168
5169 case PM_SliderControlThickness: {
5170 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_SliderHandle);
5171 if (!subRule.hasContentsSize())
5172 break;
5173 QSize size = subRule.size();
5174 return (opt->state & QStyle::State_Horizontal) ? size.height() : size.width();
5175 }
5176
5177 case PM_ToolBarIconSize:
5178 case PM_ListViewIconSize:
5179 case PM_IconViewIconSize:
5180 case PM_TabBarIconSize:
5181 case PM_MessageBoxIconSize:
5182 case PM_ButtonIconSize:
5183 case PM_SmallIconSize:
5184 if (rule.hasStyleHint(sh: "icon-size"_L1))
5185 return rule.styleHint(sh: "icon-size"_L1).toSize().width();
5186 break;
5187
5188 case PM_DockWidgetTitleMargin: {
5189 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_DockWidgetTitle);
5190 if (!subRule.hasBox())
5191 break;
5192 return (subRule.border() ? subRule.border()->borders[TopEdge] : 0)
5193 + (subRule.hasBox() ? subRule.box()->margins[TopEdge] + subRule.box()->paddings[TopEdge]: 0);
5194 }
5195
5196 case PM_DockWidgetSeparatorExtent: {
5197 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_DockWidgetSeparator);
5198 if (!subRule.hasContentsSize())
5199 break;
5200 QSize sz = subRule.size();
5201 return qMax(a: sz.width(), b: sz.height());
5202 }
5203
5204 case PM_TitleBarHeight: {
5205 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TitleBar);
5206 if (subRule.hasContentsSize())
5207 return subRule.size().height();
5208 else if (subRule.hasBox() || subRule.hasBorder()) {
5209 QFontMetrics fm = opt ? opt->fontMetrics : w->fontMetrics();
5210 return subRule.size(sz: QSize(0, fm.height())).height();
5211 }
5212 break;
5213 }
5214
5215 case PM_MdiSubWindowFrameWidth:
5216 if (rule.hasBox() || rule.hasBorder()) {
5217 return (rule.border() ? rule.border()->borders[LeftEdge] : 0)
5218 + (rule.hasBox() ? rule.box()->paddings[LeftEdge]+rule.box()->margins[LeftEdge]: 0);
5219 }
5220 break;
5221
5222 case PM_MdiSubWindowMinimizedWidth: {
5223 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, element: PseudoElement_None, state: PseudoClass_Minimized);
5224 int width = subRule.size().width();
5225 if (width != -1)
5226 return width;
5227 break;
5228 }
5229 default:
5230 break;
5231 }
5232
5233 return baseStyle()->pixelMetric(metric: m, option: opt, widget: w);
5234}
5235
5236QSize QStyleSheetStyle::sizeFromContents(ContentsType ct, const QStyleOption *opt,
5237 const QSize &csz, const QWidget *w) const
5238{
5239 RECURSION_GUARD(return baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, csz, w))
5240
5241 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, opt);
5242 QSize sz = rule.adjustSize(sz: csz);
5243
5244 switch (ct) {
5245#if QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
5246 case CT_SpinBox:
5247 if (const QStyleOptionSpinBox *spinbox = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionSpinBox *>(opt)) {
5248 if (spinbox->buttonSymbols != QAbstractSpinBox::NoButtons) {
5249 // Add some space for the up/down buttons
5250 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_SpinBoxUpButton);
5251 if (subRule.hasDrawable()) {
5252 QRect r = positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: subRule, pe: PseudoElement_SpinBoxUpButton,
5253 rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5254 sz.rwidth() += r.width();
5255 } else {
5256 QSize defaultUpSize = defaultSize(w, sz: subRule.size(), rect: spinbox->rect, pe: PseudoElement_SpinBoxUpButton);
5257 sz.rwidth() += defaultUpSize.width();
5258 }
5259 }
5260 if (rule.hasBox() || rule.hasBorder() || !rule.hasNativeBorder())
5261 sz = rule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5262 return sz;
5263 }
5264 break;
5265#endif // QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
5266 case CT_ToolButton:
5267 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder() || !rule.baseStyleCanDraw())
5268 sz += QSize(3, 3); // ### broken QToolButton
5269 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
5270 case CT_ComboBox:
5271 case CT_PushButton:
5272 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder()) {
5273 if (ct == CT_ComboBox) {
5274 //add some space for the drop down.
5275 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ComboBoxDropDown);
5276 QRect comboRect = positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: subRule, pe: PseudoElement_ComboBoxDropDown, rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5277 //+2 because there is hardcoded margins in QCommonStyle::drawControl(CE_ComboBoxLabel)
5278 sz += QSize(comboRect.width() + 2, 0);
5279 }
5280 return rule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5281 }
5282 sz = rule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, w)
5283 : QWindowsStyle::sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, widget: w);
5284 return rule.boxSize(cs: sz, flags: Margin);
5285
5286 case CT_HeaderSection: {
5287 if (const QStyleOptionHeader *hdr = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionHeader *>(opt)) {
5288 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_HeaderViewSection);
5289 if (subRule.hasGeometry() || subRule.hasBox() || !subRule.hasNativeBorder() || subRule.hasFont) {
5290 sz = subRule.adjustSize(sz: csz);
5291 if (!sz.isValid()) {
5292 // Try to set the missing values based on the base style.
5293 const auto baseSize = baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, w);
5294 if (sz.width() < 0)
5295 sz.setWidth(baseSize.width());
5296 if (sz.height() < 0)
5297 sz.setHeight(baseSize.height());
5298 }
5299 if (!subRule.hasGeometry()) {
5300 QSize nativeContentsSize;
5301 bool nullIcon = hdr->icon.isNull();
5302 const int margin = pixelMetric(m: QStyle::PM_HeaderMargin, opt: hdr, w);
5303 int iconSize = nullIcon ? 0 : pixelMetric(m: QStyle::PM_SmallIconSize, opt: hdr, w);
5304 QFontMetrics fm = hdr->fontMetrics;
5305 if (subRule.hasFont) {
5306 QFont styleFont = w ? subRule.font.resolve(w->font()) : subRule.font;
5307 fm = QFontMetrics(styleFont);
5308 }
5309 const QSize txt = fm.size(flags: 0, str: hdr->text);
5310 nativeContentsSize.setHeight(margin + qMax(a: iconSize, b: txt.height()) + margin);
5311 nativeContentsSize.setWidth((nullIcon ? 0 : margin) + iconSize
5312 + (hdr->text.isNull() ? 0 : margin) + txt.width() + margin);
5313 sz = sz.expandedTo(otherSize: nativeContentsSize);
5314 }
5315 return subRule.size(sz);
5316 }
5317 sz = subRule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, w)
5318 : QWindowsStyle::sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, widget: w);
5319 if (hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_HeaderViewDownArrow)
5320 || hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_HeaderViewUpArrow)) {
5321 const QRect arrowRect = subElementRect(r: SE_HeaderArrow, opt, widget: w);
5322 if (hdr->orientation == Qt::Horizontal)
5323 sz.rwidth() += arrowRect.width();
5324 else
5325 sz.rheight() += arrowRect.height();
5326 }
5327 return sz;
5328 }
5329 }
5330 break;
5331 case CT_GroupBox:
5332 case CT_LineEdit:
5333#if QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
5334 if (qobject_cast<QAbstractSpinBox *>(object: w ? w->parentWidget() : nullptr))
5335 return csz; // we only care about the size hint of the line edit
5336#endif
5337 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder()) {
5338 return rule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5339 }
5340 break;
5341
5342 case CT_CheckBox:
5343 case CT_RadioButton:
5344 if (const QStyleOptionButton *btn = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionButton *>(opt)) {
5345 if (rule.hasBox() || rule.hasBorder() || hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_Indicator)) {
5346 bool isRadio = (ct == CT_RadioButton);
5347 int iw = pixelMetric(m: isRadio ? PM_ExclusiveIndicatorWidth
5348 : PM_IndicatorWidth, opt: btn, w);
5349 int ih = pixelMetric(m: isRadio ? PM_ExclusiveIndicatorHeight
5350 : PM_IndicatorHeight, opt: btn, w);
5351
5352 int spacing = pixelMetric(m: isRadio ? PM_RadioButtonLabelSpacing
5353 : PM_CheckBoxLabelSpacing, opt: btn, w);
5354 sz.setWidth(sz.width() + iw + spacing);
5355 sz.setHeight(qMax(a: sz.height(), b: ih));
5356 return rule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5357 }
5358 }
5359 break;
5360
5361 case CT_Menu:
5362 case CT_MenuBar: // already has everything!
5363 case CT_ScrollBar:
5364 if (rule.hasBox() || rule.hasBorder())
5365 return sz;
5366 break;
5367
5368 case CT_MenuItem:
5369 if (const QStyleOptionMenuItem *mi = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionMenuItem *>(opt)) {
5370 PseudoElement pe = (mi->menuItemType == QStyleOptionMenuItem::Separator)
5371 ? PseudoElement_MenuSeparator : PseudoElement_Item;
5372 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: pe);
5373 if ((pe == PseudoElement_MenuSeparator) && subRule.hasContentsSize()) {
5374 return QSize(sz.width(), subRule.size().height());
5375 }
5376 if ((pe == PseudoElement_Item) && (subRule.hasBox() || subRule.hasBorder() || subRule.hasFont)) {
5377 QSize sz(csz);
5378 if (mi->text.contains(c: u'\t'))
5379 sz.rwidth() += 12; //as in QCommonStyle
5380 if (!mi->icon.isNull()) {
5381 const int pmSmall = pixelMetric(m: PM_SmallIconSize);
5382 const QSize pmSize = mi->icon.actualSize(size: QSize(pmSmall, pmSmall));
5383 sz.rwidth() += std::max(a: mi->maxIconWidth, b: pmSize.width()) + 4;
5384 } else if (mi->menuHasCheckableItems) {
5385 QRenderRule subSubRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_MenuCheckMark);
5386 QRect checkmarkRect = positionRect(w, rule1: subRule, rule2: subSubRule, pe: PseudoElement_MenuCheckMark, rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5387 sz.rwidth() += std::max(a: mi->maxIconWidth, b: checkmarkRect.width()) + 4;
5388 } else {
5389 sz.rwidth() += mi->maxIconWidth;
5390 }
5391 if (subRule.hasFont) {
5392 QFontMetrics fm(subRule.font.resolve(mi->font));
5393 const QRect r = fm.boundingRect(r: QRect(), flags: Qt::TextSingleLine | Qt::TextShowMnemonic, text: mi->text);
5394 sz = sz.expandedTo(otherSize: r.size());
5395 }
5396 return subRule.boxSize(cs: subRule.adjustSize(sz));
5397 }
5398 }
5399 break;
5400
5401 case CT_Splitter:
5402 case CT_MenuBarItem: {
5403 PseudoElement pe = (ct == CT_Splitter) ? PseudoElement_SplitterHandle : PseudoElement_Item;
5404 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: pe);
5405 if (subRule.hasBox() || subRule.hasBorder())
5406 return subRule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5407 break;
5408 }
5409
5410 case CT_ProgressBar:
5411 case CT_SizeGrip:
5412 return (rule.hasContentsSize())
5413 ? rule.size(sz)
5414 : rule.boxSize(cs: baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, w));
5415 break;
5416
5417 case CT_Slider:
5418 if (rule.hasBorder() || rule.hasBox() || rule.hasGeometry())
5419 return rule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5420 break;
5421
5422#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
5423 case CT_TabBarTab: {
5424 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TabBarTab);
5425 if (subRule.hasBox() || !subRule.hasNativeBorder() || subRule.hasFont) {
5426 int spaceForIcon = 0;
5427 bool vertical = false;
5428 QString text;
5429 if (const QStyleOptionTab *tab = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionTab *>(opt)) {
5430 if (!tab->icon.isNull())
5431 spaceForIcon = 6 /* icon offset */ + 4 /* spacing */ + 2 /* magic */; // ###: hardcoded to match with common style
5432 vertical = verticalTabs(shape: tab->shape);
5433 text = tab->text;
5434 }
5435 if (subRule.hasBox() || !subRule.hasNativeBorder())
5436 sz = csz + QSize(vertical ? 0 : spaceForIcon, vertical ? spaceForIcon : 0);
5437 if (subRule.hasFont) {
5438 // first we remove the space needed for the text using the default font
5439 const QSize oldTextSize = opt->fontMetrics.size(flags: Qt::TextShowMnemonic, str: text);
5440 (vertical ? sz.rheight() : sz.rwidth()) -= oldTextSize.width();
5441
5442 // then we add the space needed when using the rule font to the relevant
5443 // dimension, and constraint the other dimension to the maximum to make
5444 // sure we don't grow, but also don't clip icons or buttons.
5445 const QFont ruleFont = subRule.font.resolve(w->font());
5446 const QFontMetrics fm(ruleFont);
5447 const QSize textSize = fm.size(flags: Qt::TextShowMnemonic, str: text);
5448 if (vertical) {
5449 sz.rheight() += textSize.width();
5450 sz.rwidth() = qMax(a: textSize.height(), b: sz.width());
5451 } else {
5452 sz.rwidth() += textSize.width();
5453 sz.rheight() = qMax(a: textSize.height(), b: sz.height());
5454 }
5455 }
5456
5457 return subRule.boxSize(cs: subRule.adjustSize(sz));
5458 }
5459 sz = subRule.adjustSize(sz: csz);
5460 break;
5461 }
5462#endif // QT_CONFIG(tabbar)
5463
5464 case CT_MdiControls:
5465 if (const QStyleOptionComplex *ccOpt = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionComplex *>(opt)) {
5466 if (!hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiCloseButton)
5467 && !hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiNormalButton)
5468 && !hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiMinButton))
5469 break;
5470
5471 QList<QVariant> layout = rule.styleHint(sh: "button-layout"_L1).toList();
5472 if (layout.isEmpty())
5473 layout = subControlLayout(layout: "mNX"_L1);
5474
5475 int width = 0, height = 0;
5476 for (int i = 0; i < layout.size(); i++) {
5477 int layoutButton = layout[i].toInt();
5478 if (layoutButton < PseudoElement_MdiCloseButton
5479 || layoutButton > PseudoElement_MdiNormalButton)
5480 continue;
5481 QStyle::SubControl sc = knownPseudoElements[layoutButton].subControl;
5482 if (!(ccOpt->subControls & sc))
5483 continue;
5484 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: layoutButton);
5485 QSize sz = subRule.size();
5486 width += sz.width();
5487 height = qMax(a: height, b: sz.height());
5488 }
5489
5490 return QSize(width, height);
5491 }
5492 break;
5493
5494#if QT_CONFIG(itemviews)
5495 case CT_ItemViewItem: {
5496 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ViewItem);
5497 sz = baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: csz, w);
5498 sz = subRule.adjustSize(sz);
5499 if (subRule.hasBox() || subRule.hasBorder())
5500 sz = subRule.boxSize(cs: sz);
5501 return sz;
5502 }
5503#endif // QT_CONFIG(itemviews)
5504
5505 default:
5506 break;
5507 }
5508
5509 return baseStyle()->sizeFromContents(ct, opt, contentsSize: sz, w);
5510}
