5617int QStyleSheetStyle::styleHint(StyleHint sh, const QStyleOption *opt, const QWidget *w,
5618 QStyleHintReturn *shret) const
5619{
5620 RECURSION_GUARD(return baseStyle()->styleHint(sh, opt, w, shret))
5621 // Prevent endless loop if somebody use isActiveWindow property as selector.
5622 // QWidget::isActiveWindow uses this styleHint to determine if the window is active or not
5623 if (sh == SH_Widget_ShareActivation)
5624 return baseStyle()->styleHint(stylehint: sh, opt, widget: w, returnData: shret);
5625
5626 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, opt);
5627 QString s;
5628 switch (sh) {
5629 case SH_LineEdit_PasswordCharacter: s = "lineedit-password-character"_L1; break;
5630 case SH_LineEdit_PasswordMaskDelay: s = "lineedit-password-mask-delay"_L1; break;
5631 case SH_DitherDisabledText: s = "dither-disabled-text"_L1; break;
5632 case SH_EtchDisabledText: s = "etch-disabled-text"_L1; break;

5634 case SH_ItemView_ShowDecorationSelected: s = "show-decoration-selected"_L1; break;
5635 case SH_Table_GridLineColor: s = "gridline-color"_L1; break;
5636 case SH_DialogButtonLayout: s = "button-layout"_L1; break;
5637 case SH_ToolTipLabel_Opacity: s = "opacity"_L1; break;
5638 case SH_ComboBox_Popup: s = "combobox-popup"_L1; break;
5639 case SH_ComboBox_ListMouseTracking: s = "combobox-list-mousetracking"_L1; break;
5640 case SH_MenuBar_AltKeyNavigation: s = "menubar-altkey-navigation"_L1; break;
5641 case SH_Menu_Scrollable: s = "menu-scrollable"_L1; break;
5642 case SH_DrawMenuBarSeparator: s = "menubar-separator"_L1; break;
5643 case SH_MenuBar_MouseTracking: s = "mouse-tracking"_L1; break;

5645 case SH_SpinControls_DisableOnBounds: s = "spincontrol-disable-on-bounds"_L1; break;
5646 case SH_MessageBox_TextInteractionFlags: s = "messagebox-text-interaction-flags"_L1; break;

5648 case SH_ToolBox_SelectedPageTitleBold:
5649 if (renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ToolBoxTab).hasFont)
5650 return 0;
5651 break;
5652 case SH_GroupBox_TextLabelColor:
5653 if (rule.hasPalette() && rule.palette()->foreground.style() != Qt::NoBrush)

5655 break;
5656 case SH_ScrollView_FrameOnlyAroundContents: s = "scrollview-frame-around-contents"_L1; break;
5657 case SH_ScrollBar_ContextMenu: s = "scrollbar-contextmenu"_L1; break;

5662 case SH_TabBar_Alignment:

5671 break;
5672#if QT_CONFIG(tabbar)

5675 if (rule.hasPosition()) {

5679 if (align & Qt::AlignRight || align & Qt::AlignBottom)

5684 case SH_TabBar_ElideMode: s = "tabbar-elide-mode"_L1; break;
5685 case SH_TabBar_PreferNoArrows: s = "tabbar-prefer-no-arrows"_L1; break;
5686 case SH_ComboBox_PopupFrameStyle:

5690 if (view) {

5692 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: view, element: PseudoElement_None);
5693 if (subRule.hasBox() || !subRule.hasNativeBorder())

5697#endif // QT_CONFIG(combobox)
5698 break;
5699 case SH_DialogButtonBox_ButtonsHaveIcons: s = "dialogbuttonbox-buttons-have-icons"_L1; break;
5700 case SH_Workspace_FillSpaceOnMaximize: s = "mdi-fill-space-on-maximize"_L1; break;

5705 case SH_TitleBar_AutoRaise: { // plain absurd

5707 if (subRule.hasDrawable())

5715 case SH_ScrollBar_Transient:
5716 if (!rule.hasNativeBorder() || rule.hasBox() || rule.hasDrawable())

5728QRect QStyleSheetStyle::subControlRect(ComplexControl cc, const QStyleOptionComplex *opt, SubControl sc,
5729 const QWidget *w) const
5730{
5731 RECURSION_GUARD(return baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt, sc, w))
5732
5733 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: w, opt);
5734 switch (cc) {
5735 case CC_ComboBox:
5736 if (const QStyleOptionComboBox *cb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionComboBox *>(opt)) {
5737 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder()) {
5738 switch (sc) {
5739 case SC_ComboBoxFrame: return rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5740 case SC_ComboBoxEditField:
5741 {
5742 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ComboBoxDropDown);
5743 QRect r = rule.contentsRect(r: opt->rect);
5744 QRect r2 = positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: subRule, pe: PseudoElement_ComboBoxDropDown,
5745 rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5746 if (subRule.hasPosition() && subRule.position()->position & Qt::AlignLeft) {
5747 return visualRect(direction: opt->direction, boundingRect: r, logicalRect: r.adjusted(xp1: r2.width(),yp1: 0,xp2: 0,yp2: 0));
5748 } else {
5749 return visualRect(direction: opt->direction, boundingRect: r, logicalRect: r.adjusted(xp1: 0,yp1: 0,xp2: -r2.width(),yp2: 0));
5750 }
5751 }
5752 case SC_ComboBoxArrow: {
5753 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ComboBoxDropDown);
5754 return positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: subRule, pe: PseudoElement_ComboBoxDropDown, rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5755 }
5756 case SC_ComboBoxListBoxPopup:
5757 default:
5758 return baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt, sc, widget: w);
5759 }
5760 }
5761
5762 QStyleOptionComboBox comboBox(*cb);
5763 comboBox.rect = rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5764 return rule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: &comboBox, sc, widget: w)
5765 : QWindowsStyle::subControlRect(cc, opt: &comboBox, sc, w);
5766 }
5767 break;
5768
5769#if QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
5770 case CC_SpinBox:
5771 if (const QStyleOptionSpinBox *spin = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionSpinBox *>(opt)) {
5772 QRenderRule upRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_SpinBoxUpButton);
5773 QRenderRule downRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_SpinBoxDownButton);
5774 bool ruleMatch = rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder();
5775 bool upRuleMatch = upRule.hasGeometry() || upRule.hasPosition();
5776 bool downRuleMatch = downRule.hasGeometry() || downRule.hasPosition();
5777 if (ruleMatch || upRuleMatch || downRuleMatch) {
5778 switch (sc) {
5779 case SC_SpinBoxFrame:
5780 return rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5781 case SC_SpinBoxEditField:
5782 {
5783 QRect r = rule.contentsRect(r: opt->rect);
5784 // Use the widest button on each side to determine edit field size.
5785 Qt::Alignment upAlign, downAlign;
5786
5787 upAlign = upRule.hasPosition() ? upRule.position()->position
5788 : Qt::Alignment(Qt::AlignRight);
5789 upAlign = resolveAlignment(opt->direction, upAlign);
5790
5791 downAlign = downRule.hasPosition() ? downRule.position()->position
5792 : Qt::Alignment(Qt::AlignRight);
5793 downAlign = resolveAlignment(opt->direction, downAlign);
5794
5795 const bool hasButtons = (spin->buttonSymbols != QAbstractSpinBox::NoButtons);
5796 const int upSize = hasButtons
5797 ? subControlRect(cc: CC_SpinBox, opt, sc: SC_SpinBoxUp, w).width() : 0;
5798 const int downSize = hasButtons
5799 ? subControlRect(cc: CC_SpinBox, opt, sc: SC_SpinBoxDown, w).width() : 0;
5800
5801 int widestL = qMax(a: (upAlign & Qt::AlignLeft) ? upSize : 0,
5802 b: (downAlign & Qt::AlignLeft) ? downSize : 0);
5803 int widestR = qMax(a: (upAlign & Qt::AlignRight) ? upSize : 0,
5804 b: (downAlign & Qt::AlignRight) ? downSize : 0);
5805 r.setRight(r.right() - widestR);
5806 r.setLeft(r.left() + widestL);
5807 return r;
5808 }
5809 case SC_SpinBoxDown:
5810 if (downRuleMatch)
5811 return positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: downRule, pe: PseudoElement_SpinBoxDownButton,
5812 rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5813 break;
5814 case SC_SpinBoxUp:
5815 if (upRuleMatch)
5816 return positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: upRule, pe: PseudoElement_SpinBoxUpButton,
5817 rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5818 break;
5819 default:
5820 break;
5821 }
5822
5823 return baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt, sc, widget: w);
5824 }
5825
5826 QStyleOptionSpinBox spinBox(*spin);
5827 spinBox.rect = rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5828 return rule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: &spinBox, sc, widget: w)
5829 : QWindowsStyle::subControlRect(cc, opt: &spinBox, sc, w);
5830 }
5831 break;
5832#endif // QT_CONFIG(spinbox)
5833
5834 case CC_GroupBox:
5835 if (const QStyleOptionGroupBox *gb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionGroupBox *>(opt)) {
5836 switch (sc) {
5837 case SC_GroupBoxFrame:
5838 case SC_GroupBoxContents: {
5839 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder()) {
5840 return sc == SC_GroupBoxFrame ? rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect)
5841 : rule.contentsRect(r: opt->rect);
5842 }
5843 QStyleOptionGroupBox groupBox(*gb);
5844 groupBox.rect = rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5845 return baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: &groupBox, sc, widget: w);
5846 }
5847 default:
5848 case SC_GroupBoxLabel:
5849 case SC_GroupBoxCheckBox: {
5850 QRenderRule indRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_GroupBoxIndicator);
5851 QRenderRule labelRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_GroupBoxTitle);
5852 if (!labelRule.hasPosition() && !labelRule.hasGeometry() && !labelRule.hasBox()
5853 && !labelRule.hasBorder() && !indRule.hasContentsSize()) {
5854 QStyleOptionGroupBox groupBox(*gb);
5855 groupBox.rect = rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5856 return baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: &groupBox, sc, widget: w);
5857 }
5858 int tw = opt->fontMetrics.horizontalAdvance(gb->text);
5859 int th = opt->fontMetrics.height();
5860 int spacing = pixelMetric(m: QStyle::PM_CheckBoxLabelSpacing, opt, w);
5861 int iw = pixelMetric(m: QStyle::PM_IndicatorWidth, opt, w);
5862 int ih = pixelMetric(m: QStyle::PM_IndicatorHeight, opt, w);
5863
5864 if (gb->subControls & QStyle::SC_GroupBoxCheckBox) {
5865 tw = tw + iw + spacing;
5866 th = qMax(a: th, b: ih);
5867 }
5868 if (!labelRule.hasGeometry()) {
5869 labelRule.geo = new QStyleSheetGeometryData(tw, th, tw, th, -1, -1);
5870 } else {
5871 labelRule.geo->width = tw;
5872 labelRule.geo->height = th;
5873 }
5874 if (!labelRule.hasPosition()) {
5875 labelRule.p = new QStyleSheetPositionData(0, 0, 0, 0, defaultOrigin(pe: PseudoElement_GroupBoxTitle),
5876 gb->textAlignment, PositionMode_Static);
5877 }
5878 QRect r = positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: labelRule, pe: PseudoElement_GroupBoxTitle,
5879 rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5880 if (gb->subControls & SC_GroupBoxCheckBox) {
5881 r = labelRule.contentsRect(r);
5882 if (sc == SC_GroupBoxLabel) {
5883 r.setLeft(r.left() + iw + spacing);
5884 r.setTop(r.center().y() - th/2);
5885 } else {
5886 r = QRect(r.left(), r.center().y() - ih/2, iw, ih);
5887 }
5888 return r;
5889 } else {
5890 return labelRule.contentsRect(r);
5891 }
5892 }
5893 } // switch
5894 }
5895 break;
5896
5897 case CC_ToolButton:
5898 if (const QStyleOptionToolButton *tb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionToolButton *>(opt)) {
5899 if (rule.hasBox() || !rule.hasNativeBorder()) {
5900 switch (sc) {
5901 case SC_ToolButton: return rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5902 case SC_ToolButtonMenu: {
5903 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ToolButtonMenu);
5904 return positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: subRule, pe: PseudoElement_ToolButtonMenu, rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
5905 }
5906 default:
5907 break;
5908 }
5909 }
5910
5911 QStyleOptionToolButton tool(*tb);
5912 tool.rect = rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5913 return rule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: &tool, sc, widget: w)
5914 : QWindowsStyle::subControlRect(cc, opt: &tool, sc, w);
5915 }
5916 break;
5917
5918#if QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
5919 case CC_ScrollBar:
5920 if (const QStyleOptionSlider *sb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionSlider *>(opt)) {
5921 QStyleOptionSlider styleOptionSlider(*sb);
5922 styleOptionSlider.rect = rule.borderRect(r: opt->rect);
5923 if (rule.hasDrawable() || rule.hasBox()) {
5924 QRect grooveRect;
5925 if (!rule.hasBox()) {
5926 grooveRect = rule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: sb, sc: SC_ScrollBarGroove, widget: w)
5927 : QWindowsStyle::subControlRect(cc, opt: sb, sc: SC_ScrollBarGroove, w);
5928 } else {
5929 grooveRect = rule.contentsRect(r: opt->rect);
5930 }
5931
5932 PseudoElement pe = PseudoElement_None;
5933
5934 switch (sc) {
5935 case SC_ScrollBarGroove:
5936 return grooveRect;
5937 case SC_ScrollBarAddPage:
5938 case SC_ScrollBarSubPage:
5939 case SC_ScrollBarSlider: {
5940 QRect contentRect = grooveRect;
5941 if (hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider)) {
5942 QRenderRule sliderRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider);
5943 Origin origin = sliderRule.hasPosition() ? sliderRule.position()->origin : defaultOrigin(pe: PseudoElement_ScrollBarSlider);
5944 contentRect = rule.originRect(rect: opt->rect, origin);
5945 }
5946 int maxlen = (styleOptionSlider.orientation == Qt::Horizontal) ? contentRect.width() : contentRect.height();
5947 int sliderlen;
5948 if (sb->maximum != sb->minimum) {
5949 uint range = sb->maximum - sb->minimum;
5950 sliderlen = (qint64(sb->pageStep) * maxlen) / (range + sb->pageStep);
5951
5952 int slidermin = pixelMetric(m: PM_ScrollBarSliderMin, opt: sb, w);
5953 if (sliderlen < slidermin || range > INT_MAX / 2)
5954 sliderlen = slidermin;
5955 if (sliderlen > maxlen)
5956 sliderlen = maxlen;
5957 } else {
5958 sliderlen = maxlen;
5959 }
5960 int sliderstart = (styleOptionSlider.orientation == Qt::Horizontal ? contentRect.left() : contentRect.top())
5961 + sliderPositionFromValue(min: sb->minimum, max: sb->maximum, val: sb->sliderPosition,
5962 space: maxlen - sliderlen, upsideDown: sb->upsideDown);
5963
5964 QRect sr = (sb->orientation == Qt::Horizontal)
5965 ? QRect(sliderstart, contentRect.top(), sliderlen, contentRect.height())
5966 : QRect(contentRect.left(), sliderstart, contentRect.width(), sliderlen);
5967 if (sc == SC_ScrollBarSubPage)
5968 sr = QRect(contentRect.topLeft(), sb->orientation == Qt::Horizontal ? sr.bottomLeft() : sr.topRight());
5969 else if (sc == SC_ScrollBarAddPage)
5970 sr = QRect(sb->orientation == Qt::Horizontal ? sr.topRight() : sr.bottomLeft(), contentRect.bottomRight());
5971 return visualRect(direction: styleOptionSlider.direction, boundingRect: grooveRect, logicalRect: sr);
5972 }
5973 case SC_ScrollBarAddLine: pe = PseudoElement_ScrollBarAddLine; break;
5974 case SC_ScrollBarSubLine: pe = PseudoElement_ScrollBarSubLine; break;
5975 case SC_ScrollBarFirst: pe = PseudoElement_ScrollBarFirst; break;
5976 case SC_ScrollBarLast: pe = PseudoElement_ScrollBarLast; break;
5977 default: break;
5978 }
5979 if (hasStyleRule(obj: w,part: pe)) {
5980 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: pe);
5981 if (subRule.hasPosition() || subRule.hasGeometry() || subRule.hasBox()) {
5982 const QStyleSheetPositionData *pos = subRule.position();
5983 QRect originRect = grooveRect;
5984 if (rule.hasBox()) {
5985 Origin origin = (pos && pos->origin != Origin_Unknown) ? pos->origin : defaultOrigin(pe);
5986 originRect = rule.originRect(rect: opt->rect, origin);
5987 }
5988 return positionRect(w, rule2: subRule, pe, originRect, dir: styleOptionSlider.direction);
5989 }
5990 }
5991 }
5992 return rule.baseStyleCanDraw() ? baseStyle()->subControlRect(cc, opt: &styleOptionSlider, sc, widget: w)
5993 : QWindowsStyle::subControlRect(cc, opt: &styleOptionSlider, sc, w);
5994 }
5995 break;
5996#endif // QT_CONFIG(scrollbar)
5997
5998#if QT_CONFIG(slider)
5999 case CC_Slider:
6000 if (const QStyleOptionSlider *slider = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionSlider *>(opt)) {
6001 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_SliderGroove);
6002 if (!subRule.hasDrawable())
6003 break;
6004 subRule.img = nullptr;
6005 QRect gr = positionRect(w, rule1: rule, rule2: subRule, pe: PseudoElement_SliderGroove, rect: opt->rect, dir: opt->direction);
6006 switch (sc) {
6007 case SC_SliderGroove:
6008 return gr;
6009 case SC_SliderHandle: {
6010 bool horizontal = slider->orientation & Qt::Horizontal;
6011 QRect cr = subRule.contentsRect(r: gr);
6012 QRenderRule subRule2 = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_SliderHandle);
6013 int len = horizontal ? subRule2.size().width() : subRule2.size().height();
6014 subRule2.img = nullptr;
6015 subRule2.geo = nullptr;
6016 cr = positionRect(w, rule2: subRule2, pe: PseudoElement_SliderHandle, originRect: cr, dir: opt->direction);
6017 int thickness = horizontal ? cr.height() : cr.width();
6018 int sliderPos = sliderPositionFromValue(min: slider->minimum, max: slider->maximum, val: slider->sliderPosition,
6019 space: (horizontal ? cr.width() : cr.height()) - len, upsideDown: slider->upsideDown);
6020 cr = horizontal ? QRect(cr.x() + sliderPos, cr.y(), len, thickness)
6021 : QRect(cr.x(), cr.y() + sliderPos, thickness, len);
6022 return subRule2.borderRect(r: cr);
6023 break; }
6024 case SC_SliderTickmarks:
6025 // TODO...

6028 }
6029 }

6031#endif // QT_CONFIG(slider)

6033 case CC_MdiControls:
6034 if (hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiCloseButton)
6035 || hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiNormalButton)
6036 || hasStyleRule(obj: w, part: PseudoElement_MdiMinButton)) {
6037 QList<QVariant> layout = rule.styleHint(sh: "button-layout"_L1).toList();
6038 if (layout.isEmpty())
6039 layout = subControlLayout(layout: "mNX"_L1);
6040
6041 int x = 0, width = 0;
6042 QRenderRule subRule;
6043 for (int i = 0; i < layout.size(); i++) {
6044 int layoutButton = layout[i].toInt();
6045 if (layoutButton < PseudoElement_MdiCloseButton
6046 || layoutButton > PseudoElement_MdiNormalButton)
6047 continue;
6048 QStyle::SubControl control = knownPseudoElements[layoutButton].subControl;
6049 if (!(opt->subControls & control))
6050 continue;
6051 subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: layoutButton);
6052 width = subRule.size().width();
6053 if (sc == control)
6054 break;
6055 x += width;
6056 }
6057
6058 return subRule.borderRect(r: QRect(x, opt->rect.top(), width, opt->rect.height()));
6059 }
6060 break;
6061
6062 case CC_TitleBar:
6063 if (const QStyleOptionTitleBar *tb = qstyleoption_cast<const QStyleOptionTitleBar *>(opt)) {
6064 QRenderRule subRule = renderRule(obj: w, opt, pseudoElement: PseudoElement_TitleBar);
6065 if (!subRule.hasDrawable() && !subRule.hasBox() && !subRule.hasBorder())
6066 break;

6068 return layoutRects.value(key: sc);

6070 break;

6072 default:

6359void QStyleSheetStyle::updateStyleSheetFont(QWidget* w) const
6360{
6361 // Qt's fontDialog relies on the font of the sample edit for its selection,
6362 // we should never override it.
6363 if (w->objectName() == "qt_fontDialog_sampleEdit"_L1)
6364 return;
6365
6366 QWidget *container = containerWidget(w);
6367 QRenderRule rule = renderRule(obj: container, element: PseudoElement_None,
6368 state: PseudoClass_Active | PseudoClass_Enabled | extendedPseudoClass(w: container));
6369
6370 const bool useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles =
6371 QCoreApplication::testAttribute(attribute: Qt::AA_UseStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles);
6372
6373 if (useStyleSheetPropagationInWidgetStyles) {
6374 unsetStyleSheetFont(w);
6375
6376 if (rule.font.resolveMask()) {
6377 QFont wf = w->d_func()->localFont();
6378 styleSheetCaches->customFontWidgets.insert(key: w, value: {.oldWidgetValue: wf, .resolveMask: rule.font.resolveMask()});
6379
6380 QFont font = rule.font.resolve(wf);
6381 font.setResolveMask(wf.resolveMask() | rule.font.resolveMask());
6382 w->setFont(font);
6383 }
6384 } else {
6385 QFont wf = w->d_func()->localFont();
6386 QFont font = rule.font.resolve(wf);
6387 font.setResolveMask(wf.resolveMask() | rule.font.resolveMask());
6388
6389 if ((!w->isWindow() || w->testAttribute(attribute: Qt::WA_WindowPropagation))
6390 && isNaturalChild(obj: w) && qobject_cast<QWidget *>(o: w->parent())) {
6391
6392 font = font.resolve(static_cast<QWidget *>(w->parent())->font());
6393 }
6394
6395 if (wf.resolveMask() == font.resolveMask() && wf == font)
6396 return;
6397
6398 w->data->fnt = font;
6399 w->d_func()->directFontResolveMask = font.resolveMask();
6400
6401 QEvent e(QEvent::FontChange);
6402 QCoreApplication::sendEvent(receiver: w, event: &e);
6403 }
6404}

6416// Polish palette that should be used for a particular widget, with particular states
6417// (eg. :focus, :hover, ...)
6418// this is called by widgets that paint themself in their paint event
6419// Returns \c true if there is a new palette in pal.
6420bool QStyleSheetStyle::styleSheetPalette(const QWidget* w, const QStyleOption* opt, QPalette* pal)

6437Qt::Alignment QStyleSheetStyle::resolveAlignment(Qt::LayoutDirection layDir, Qt::Alignment src)
6438{
6439 if (layDir == Qt::LeftToRight || src & Qt::AlignAbsolute)
6440 return src;
6441
6442 if (src & Qt::AlignLeft) {
6443 src &= ~Qt::AlignLeft;
6444 src |= Qt::AlignRight;
6445 } else if (src & Qt::AlignRight) {
6446 src &= ~Qt::AlignRight;
6447 src |= Qt::AlignLeft;
6448 }
6449 src |= Qt::AlignAbsolute;
6450 return src;
6451}

6467QPixmap QStyleSheetStyle::loadPixmap(const QString &fileName, const QObject *context)
6468{
6469 qreal ratio = -1.0;
6470 if (const QWidget *widget = qobject_cast<const QWidget *>(o: context)) {
6471 if (QScreen *screen = QApplication::screenAt(point: widget->mapToGlobal(QPoint(0, 0))))
6472 ratio = screen->devicePixelRatio();
6473 }
6474
6475 if (ratio < 0) {
6476 if (const QApplication *app = qApp)
6477 ratio = app->devicePixelRatio();
6478 else
6479 ratio = 1.0;
6480 }
6481
6482 qreal sourceDevicePixelRatio = 1.0;
6483 QString resolvedFileName = qt_findAtNxFile(baseFileName: fileName, targetDevicePixelRatio: ratio, sourceDevicePixelRatio: &sourceDevicePixelRatio);
6484 QPixmap pixmap(resolvedFileName);
6485 pixmap.setDevicePixelRatio(sourceDevicePixelRatio);
6486 return pixmap;
6487}
